49/*
50 * used by extent splitting.
51 */
52#define EXT4_EXT_MAY_ZEROOUT 0x1 /* safe to zeroout if split fails \
53 due to ENOSPC */
54#define EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT1 0x2 /* mark first half unwritten */
55#define EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT2 0x4 /* mark second half unwritten */
56
57#define EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID1 0x8 /* first half contains valid data */
58#define EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID2 0x10 /* second half contains valid data */

60static __le32 ext4_extent_block_csum(struct inode *inode,
61 struct ext4_extent_header *eh)
62{
63 struct ext4_inode_info *ei = EXT4_I(inode);
64 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb);
65 __u32 csum;
66
67 csum = ext4_chksum(sbi, ei->i_csum_seed, (__u8 *)eh,
68 EXT4_EXTENT_TAIL_OFFSET(eh));
69 return cpu_to_le32(csum);
70}
71
72static int ext4_extent_block_csum_verify(struct inode *inode,
73 struct ext4_extent_header *eh)
74{
75 struct ext4_extent_tail *et;
76
77 if (!ext4_has_metadata_csum(inode->i_sb))
78 return 1;
79
80 et = find_ext4_extent_tail(eh);
81 if (et->et_checksum != ext4_extent_block_csum(inode, eh))
82 return 0;
83 return 1;
84}
85
86static void ext4_extent_block_csum_set(struct inode *inode,
87 struct ext4_extent_header *eh)
88{
89 struct ext4_extent_tail *et;
90
91 if (!ext4_has_metadata_csum(inode->i_sb))
92 return;
93
94 et = find_ext4_extent_tail(eh);
95 et->et_checksum = ext4_extent_block_csum(inode, eh);
96}

115static int ext4_ext_truncate_extend_restart(handle_t *handle,
116 struct inode *inode,
117 int needed)
118{
119 int err;
120
121 if (!ext4_handle_valid(handle))
122 return 0;
123 if (handle->h_buffer_credits >= needed)
124 return 0;
125 /*
126 * If we need to extend the journal get a few extra blocks
127 * while we're at it for efficiency's sake.
128 */
129 needed += 3;
130 err = ext4_journal_extend(handle, needed - handle->h_buffer_credits);
131 if (err <= 0)
132 return err;
133 err = ext4_truncate_restart_trans(handle, inode, needed);
134 if (err == 0)
135 err = -EAGAIN;
136
137 return err;
138}

140/*
141 * could return:
142 * - EROFS
143 * - ENOMEM
144 */
145static int ext4_ext_get_access(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
146 struct ext4_ext_path *path)
147{
148 if (path->p_bh) {
149 /* path points to block */
150 BUFFER_TRACE(path->p_bh, "get_write_access");
151 return ext4_journal_get_write_access(handle, path->p_bh);
152 }
153 /* path points to leaf/index in inode body */
154 /* we use in-core data, no need to protect them */
155 return 0;
156}
157
158/*
159 * could return:
160 * - EROFS
161 * - ENOMEM
162 * - EIO
163 */
164int __ext4_ext_dirty(const char *where, unsigned int line, handle_t *handle,
165 struct inode *inode, struct ext4_ext_path *path)
166{
167 int err;
168
169 WARN_ON(!rwsem_is_locked(&EXT4_I(inode)->i_data_sem));
170 if (path->p_bh) {
171 ext4_extent_block_csum_set(inode, ext_block_hdr(path->p_bh));
172 /* path points to block */
173 err = __ext4_handle_dirty_metadata(where, line, handle,
174 inode, path->p_bh);
175 } else {
176 /* path points to leaf/index in inode body */
177 err = ext4_mark_inode_dirty(handle, inode);
178 }
179 return err;
180}

182static ext4_fsblk_t ext4_ext_find_goal(struct inode *inode,
183 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
184 ext4_lblk_t block)
185{
186 if (path) {
187 int depth = path->p_depth;
188 struct ext4_extent *ex;
189
190 /*
191 * Try to predict block placement assuming that we are
192 * filling in a file which will eventually be
193 * non-sparse --- i.e., in the case of libbfd writing
194 * an ELF object sections out-of-order but in a way
195 * the eventually results in a contiguous object or
196 * executable file, or some database extending a table
197 * space file. However, this is actually somewhat
198 * non-ideal if we are writing a sparse file such as
199 * qemu or KVM writing a raw image file that is going
200 * to stay fairly sparse, since it will end up
201 * fragmenting the file system's free space. Maybe we
202 * should have some hueristics or some way to allow
203 * userspace to pass a hint to file system,
204 * especially if the latter case turns out to be
205 * common.
206 */
207 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
208 if (ex) {
209 ext4_fsblk_t ext_pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex);
210 ext4_lblk_t ext_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
211
212 if (block > ext_block)
213 return ext_pblk + (block - ext_block);
214 else
215 return ext_pblk - (ext_block - block);
216 }
217
218 /* it looks like index is empty;
219 * try to find starting block from index itself */
220 if (path[depth].p_bh)
221 return path[depth].p_bh->b_blocknr;
222 }
223
224 /* OK. use inode's group */
225 return ext4_inode_to_goal_block(inode);
226}
227
228/*
229 * Allocation for a meta data block
230 */
231static ext4_fsblk_t
232ext4_ext_new_meta_block(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
233 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
234 struct ext4_extent *ex, int *err, unsigned int flags)
235{
236 ext4_fsblk_t goal, newblock;
237
238 goal = ext4_ext_find_goal(inode, path, le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block));
239 newblock = ext4_new_meta_blocks(handle, inode, goal, flags,
240 NULL, err);
241 return newblock;
242}

244static inline int ext4_ext_space_block(struct inode *inode, int check)
245{
246 int size;
247
248 size = (inode->i_sb->s_blocksize - sizeof(struct ext4_extent_header))
249 / sizeof(struct ext4_extent);
250#ifdef AGGRESSIVE_TEST
251 if (!check && size > 6)
252 size = 6;
253#endif
254 return size;
255}
256
257static inline int ext4_ext_space_block_idx(struct inode *inode, int check)
258{
259 int size;
260
261 size = (inode->i_sb->s_blocksize - sizeof(struct ext4_extent_header))
262 / sizeof(struct ext4_extent_idx);
263#ifdef AGGRESSIVE_TEST
264 if (!check && size > 5)
265 size = 5;
266#endif
267 return size;
268}
269
270static inline int ext4_ext_space_root(struct inode *inode, int check)
271{
272 int size;
273
274 size = sizeof(EXT4_I(inode)->i_data);
275 size -= sizeof(struct ext4_extent_header);
276 size /= sizeof(struct ext4_extent);
277#ifdef AGGRESSIVE_TEST
278 if (!check && size > 3)
279 size = 3;
280#endif
281 return size;
282}
283
284static inline int ext4_ext_space_root_idx(struct inode *inode, int check)
285{
286 int size;
287
288 size = sizeof(EXT4_I(inode)->i_data);
289 size -= sizeof(struct ext4_extent_header);
290 size /= sizeof(struct ext4_extent_idx);
291#ifdef AGGRESSIVE_TEST
292 if (!check && size > 4)
293 size = 4;
294#endif
295 return size;
296}

298static inline int
299ext4_force_split_extent_at(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
300 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath, ext4_lblk_t lblk,
301 int nofail)
302{
303 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
304 int unwritten = ext4_ext_is_unwritten(path[path->p_depth].p_ext);
305
306 return ext4_split_extent_at(handle, inode, ppath, lblk, unwritten ?
307 EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT1|EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT2 : 0,
308 EXT4_EX_NOCACHE | EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_PRE_IO |
309 (nofail ? EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_METADATA_NOFAIL:0));
310}

312/*
313 * Calculate the number of metadata blocks needed
314 * to allocate @blocks
315 * Worse case is one block per extent
316 */
317int ext4_ext_calc_metadata_amount(struct inode *inode, ext4_lblk_t lblock)
318{
319 struct ext4_inode_info *ei = EXT4_I(inode);
320 int idxs;
321
322 idxs = ((inode->i_sb->s_blocksize - sizeof(struct ext4_extent_header))
323 / sizeof(struct ext4_extent_idx));
324
325 /*
326 * If the new delayed allocation block is contiguous with the
327 * previous da block, it can share index blocks with the
328 * previous block, so we only need to allocate a new index
329 * block every idxs leaf blocks. At ldxs**2 blocks, we need
330 * an additional index block, and at ldxs**3 blocks, yet
331 * another index blocks.
332 */
333 if (ei->i_da_metadata_calc_len &&
334 ei->i_da_metadata_calc_last_lblock+1 == lblock) {
335 int num = 0;
336
337 if ((ei->i_da_metadata_calc_len % idxs) == 0)
338 num++;
339 if ((ei->i_da_metadata_calc_len % (idxs*idxs)) == 0)
340 num++;
341 if ((ei->i_da_metadata_calc_len % (idxs*idxs*idxs)) == 0) {
342 num++;
343 ei->i_da_metadata_calc_len = 0;
344 } else
345 ei->i_da_metadata_calc_len++;
346 ei->i_da_metadata_calc_last_lblock++;
347 return num;
348 }
349
350 /*
351 * In the worst case we need a new set of index blocks at
352 * every level of the inode's extent tree.
353 */
354 ei->i_da_metadata_calc_len = 1;
355 ei->i_da_metadata_calc_last_lblock = lblock;
356 return ext_depth(inode) + 1;
357}
358
359static int
360ext4_ext_max_entries(struct inode *inode, int depth)
361{
362 int max;
363
364 if (depth == ext_depth(inode)) {
365 if (depth == 0)
366 max = ext4_ext_space_root(inode, 1);
367 else
368 max = ext4_ext_space_root_idx(inode, 1);
369 } else {
370 if (depth == 0)
371 max = ext4_ext_space_block(inode, 1);
372 else
373 max = ext4_ext_space_block_idx(inode, 1);
374 }
375
376 return max;
377}

379static int ext4_valid_extent(struct inode *inode, struct ext4_extent *ext)
380{
381 ext4_fsblk_t block = ext4_ext_pblock(ext);
382 int len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ext);
383 ext4_lblk_t lblock = le32_to_cpu(ext->ee_block);
384
385 /*
386 * We allow neither:
387 * - zero length
388 * - overflow/wrap-around
389 */
390 if (lblock + len <= lblock)
391 return 0;
392 return ext4_data_block_valid(EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb), block, len);
393}
394
395static int ext4_valid_extent_idx(struct inode *inode,
396 struct ext4_extent_idx *ext_idx)
397{
398 ext4_fsblk_t block = ext4_idx_pblock(ext_idx);
399
400 return ext4_data_block_valid(EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb), block, 1);
401}
402
403static int ext4_valid_extent_entries(struct inode *inode,
404 struct ext4_extent_header *eh,
405 int depth)
406{
407 unsigned short entries;
408 if (eh->eh_entries == 0)
409 return 1;
410
411 entries = le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries);
412
413 if (depth == 0) {
414 /* leaf entries */
415 struct ext4_extent *ext = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh);
416 struct ext4_super_block *es = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb)->s_es;
417 ext4_fsblk_t pblock = 0;
418 ext4_lblk_t lblock = 0;
419 ext4_lblk_t prev = 0;
420 int len = 0;
421 while (entries) {
422 if (!ext4_valid_extent(inode, ext))
423 return 0;
424
425 /* Check for overlapping extents */
426 lblock = le32_to_cpu(ext->ee_block);
427 len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ext);
428 if ((lblock <= prev) && prev) {
429 pblock = ext4_ext_pblock(ext);
430 es->s_last_error_block = cpu_to_le64(pblock);
431 return 0;
432 }
433 ext++;
434 entries--;
435 prev = lblock + len - 1;
436 }
437 } else {
438 struct ext4_extent_idx *ext_idx = EXT_FIRST_INDEX(eh);
439 while (entries) {
440 if (!ext4_valid_extent_idx(inode, ext_idx))
441 return 0;
442 ext_idx++;
443 entries--;
444 }
445 }
446 return 1;
447}

449static int __ext4_ext_check(const char *function, unsigned int line,
450 struct inode *inode, struct ext4_extent_header *eh,
451 int depth, ext4_fsblk_t pblk)
452{
453 const char *error_msg;
454 int max = 0, err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
455
456 if (unlikely(eh->eh_magic != EXT4_EXT_MAGIC)) {
457 error_msg = "invalid magic";
458 goto corrupted;
459 }
460 if (unlikely(le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_depth) != depth)) {
461 error_msg = "unexpected eh_depth";
462 goto corrupted;
463 }
464 if (unlikely(eh->eh_max == 0)) {
465 error_msg = "invalid eh_max";
466 goto corrupted;
467 }
468 max = ext4_ext_max_entries(inode, depth);
469 if (unlikely(le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_max) > max)) {
470 error_msg = "too large eh_max";
471 goto corrupted;
472 }
473 if (unlikely(le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries) > le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_max))) {
474 error_msg = "invalid eh_entries";
475 goto corrupted;
476 }
477 if (!ext4_valid_extent_entries(inode, eh, depth)) {
478 error_msg = "invalid extent entries";
479 goto corrupted;
480 }
481 if (unlikely(depth > 32)) {
482 error_msg = "too large eh_depth";
483 goto corrupted;
484 }
485 /* Verify checksum on non-root extent tree nodes */
486 if (ext_depth(inode) != depth &&
487 !ext4_extent_block_csum_verify(inode, eh)) {
488 error_msg = "extent tree corrupted";
489 err = -EFSBADCRC;
490 goto corrupted;
491 }
492 return 0;
493
494corrupted:
495 ext4_error_inode(inode, function, line, 0,
496 "pblk %llu bad header/extent: %s - magic %x, "
497 "entries %u, max %u(%u), depth %u(%u)",
498 (unsigned long long) pblk, error_msg,
499 le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_magic),
500 le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries), le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_max),
501 max, le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_depth), depth);
502 return err;
503}
504
505#define ext4_ext_check(inode, eh, depth, pblk) \
506 __ext4_ext_check(__func__, __LINE__, (inode), (eh), (depth), (pblk))
507
508int ext4_ext_check_inode(struct inode *inode)
509{
510 return ext4_ext_check(inode, ext_inode_hdr(inode), ext_depth(inode), 0);
511}

513static struct buffer_head *
514__read_extent_tree_block(const char *function, unsigned int line,
515 struct inode *inode, ext4_fsblk_t pblk, int depth,
516 int flags)
517{
518 struct buffer_head *bh;
519 int err;
520
521 bh = sb_getblk_gfp(inode->i_sb, pblk, __GFP_MOVABLE | GFP_NOFS);
522 if (unlikely(!bh))
523 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
524
525 if (!bh_uptodate_or_lock(bh)) {
526 trace_ext4_ext_load_extent(inode, pblk, _RET_IP_);
527 err = bh_submit_read(bh);
528 if (err < 0)
529 goto errout;
530 }
531 if (buffer_verified(bh) && !(flags & EXT4_EX_FORCE_CACHE))
532 return bh;
533 err = __ext4_ext_check(function, line, inode,
534 ext_block_hdr(bh), depth, pblk);
535 if (err)
536 goto errout;
537 set_buffer_verified(bh);
538 /*
539 * If this is a leaf block, cache all of its entries
540 */
541 if (!(flags & EXT4_EX_NOCACHE) && depth == 0) {
542 struct ext4_extent_header *eh = ext_block_hdr(bh);
543 struct ext4_extent *ex = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh);
544 ext4_lblk_t prev = 0;
545 int i;
546
547 for (i = le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries); i > 0; i--, ex++) {
548 unsigned int status = EXTENT_STATUS_WRITTEN;
549 ext4_lblk_t lblk = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
550 int len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
551
552 if (prev && (prev != lblk))
553 ext4_es_cache_extent(inode, prev,
554 lblk - prev, ~0,
555 EXTENT_STATUS_HOLE);
556
557 if (ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex))
558 status = EXTENT_STATUS_UNWRITTEN;
559 ext4_es_cache_extent(inode, lblk, len,
560 ext4_ext_pblock(ex), status);
561 prev = lblk + len;
562 }
563 }
564 return bh;
565errout:
566 put_bh(bh);
567 return ERR_PTR(err);
568
569}
570
571#define read_extent_tree_block(inode, pblk, depth, flags) \
572 __read_extent_tree_block(__func__, __LINE__, (inode), (pblk), \
573 (depth), (flags))

575/*
576 * This function is called to cache a file's extent information in the
577 * extent status tree
578 */
579int ext4_ext_precache(struct inode *inode)
580{
581 struct ext4_inode_info *ei = EXT4_I(inode);
582 struct ext4_ext_path *path = NULL;
583 struct buffer_head *bh;
584 int i = 0, depth, ret = 0;
585
586 if (!ext4_test_inode_flag(inode, EXT4_INODE_EXTENTS))
587 return 0; /* not an extent-mapped inode */
588
589 down_read(&ei->i_data_sem);
590 depth = ext_depth(inode);
591
592 path = kzalloc(sizeof(struct ext4_ext_path) * (depth + 1),
593 GFP_NOFS);
594 if (path == NULL) {
595 up_read(&ei->i_data_sem);
596 return -ENOMEM;
597 }
598
599 /* Don't cache anything if there are no external extent blocks */
600 if (depth == 0)
601 goto out;
602 path[0].p_hdr = ext_inode_hdr(inode);
603 ret = ext4_ext_check(inode, path[0].p_hdr, depth, 0);
604 if (ret)
605 goto out;
606 path[0].p_idx = EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path[0].p_hdr);
607 while (i >= 0) {
608 /*
609 * If this is a leaf block or we've reached the end of
610 * the index block, go up
611 */
612 if ((i == depth) ||
613 path[i].p_idx > EXT_LAST_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr)) {
614 brelse(path[i].p_bh);
615 path[i].p_bh = NULL;
616 i--;
617 continue;
618 }
619 bh = read_extent_tree_block(inode,
620 ext4_idx_pblock(path[i].p_idx++),
621 depth - i - 1,
622 EXT4_EX_FORCE_CACHE);
623 if (IS_ERR(bh)) {
624 ret = PTR_ERR(bh);
625 break;
626 }
627 i++;
628 path[i].p_bh = bh;
629 path[i].p_hdr = ext_block_hdr(bh);
630 path[i].p_idx = EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr);
631 }
632 ext4_set_inode_state(inode, EXT4_STATE_EXT_PRECACHED);
633out:
634 up_read(&ei->i_data_sem);
635 ext4_ext_drop_refs(path);
636 kfree(path);
637 return ret;
638}

640#ifdef EXT_DEBUG
641static void ext4_ext_show_path(struct inode *inode, struct ext4_ext_path *path)
642{
643 int k, l = path->p_depth;
644
645 ext_debug("path:");
646 for (k = 0; k <= l; k++, path++) {
647 if (path->p_idx) {
648 ext_debug(" %d->%llu", le32_to_cpu(path->p_idx->ei_block),
649 ext4_idx_pblock(path->p_idx));
650 } else if (path->p_ext) {
651 ext_debug(" %d:[%d]%d:%llu ",
652 le32_to_cpu(path->p_ext->ee_block),
653 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(path->p_ext),
654 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(path->p_ext),
655 ext4_ext_pblock(path->p_ext));
656 } else
657 ext_debug(" []");
658 }
659 ext_debug("\n");
660}

662static void ext4_ext_show_leaf(struct inode *inode, struct ext4_ext_path *path)
663{
664 int depth = ext_depth(inode);
665 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
666 struct ext4_extent *ex;
667 int i;
668
669 if (!path)
670 return;
671
672 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
673 ex = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh);
674
675 ext_debug("Displaying leaf extents for inode %lu\n", inode->i_ino);
676
677 for (i = 0; i < le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries); i++, ex++) {
678 ext_debug("%d:[%d]%d:%llu ", le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block),
679 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex),
680 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex), ext4_ext_pblock(ex));
681 }
682 ext_debug("\n");
683}

685static void ext4_ext_show_move(struct inode *inode, struct ext4_ext_path *path,
686 ext4_fsblk_t newblock, int level)
687{
688 int depth = ext_depth(inode);
689 struct ext4_extent *ex;
690
691 if (depth != level) {
692 struct ext4_extent_idx *idx;
693 idx = path[level].p_idx;
694 while (idx <= EXT_MAX_INDEX(path[level].p_hdr)) {
695 ext_debug("%d: move %d:%llu in new index %llu\n", level,
696 le32_to_cpu(idx->ei_block),
697 ext4_idx_pblock(idx),
698 newblock);
699 idx++;
700 }
701
702 return;
703 }
704
705 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
706 while (ex <= EXT_MAX_EXTENT(path[depth].p_hdr)) {
707 ext_debug("move %d:%llu:[%d]%d in new leaf %llu\n",
708 le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block),
709 ext4_ext_pblock(ex),
710 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex),
711 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex),
712 newblock);
713 ex++;
714 }
715}
716
717#else
718#define ext4_ext_show_path(inode, path)
719#define ext4_ext_show_leaf(inode, path)
720#define ext4_ext_show_move(inode, path, newblock, level)
721#endif
722
723void ext4_ext_drop_refs(struct ext4_ext_path *path)
724{
725 int depth, i;
726
727 if (!path)
728 return;
729 depth = path->p_depth;
730 for (i = 0; i <= depth; i++, path++)
731 if (path->p_bh) {
732 brelse(path->p_bh);
733 path->p_bh = NULL;
734 }
735}
736
737/*
738 * ext4_ext_binsearch_idx:
739 * binary search for the closest index of the given block
740 * the header must be checked before calling this
741 */
742static void
743ext4_ext_binsearch_idx(struct inode *inode,
744 struct ext4_ext_path *path, ext4_lblk_t block)
745{
746 struct ext4_extent_header *eh = path->p_hdr;
747 struct ext4_extent_idx *r, *l, *m;
748
749
750 ext_debug("binsearch for %u(idx): ", block);
751
752 l = EXT_FIRST_INDEX(eh) + 1;
753 r = EXT_LAST_INDEX(eh);
754 while (l <= r) {
755 m = l + (r - l) / 2;
756 if (block < le32_to_cpu(m->ei_block))
757 r = m - 1;
758 else
759 l = m + 1;
760 ext_debug("%p(%u):%p(%u):%p(%u) ", l, le32_to_cpu(l->ei_block),
761 m, le32_to_cpu(m->ei_block),
762 r, le32_to_cpu(r->ei_block));
763 }
764
765 path->p_idx = l - 1;
766 ext_debug(" -> %u->%lld ", le32_to_cpu(path->p_idx->ei_block),
767 ext4_idx_pblock(path->p_idx));
768
769#ifdef CHECK_BINSEARCH
770 {
771 struct ext4_extent_idx *chix, *ix;
772 int k;
773
774 chix = ix = EXT_FIRST_INDEX(eh);
775 for (k = 0; k < le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries); k++, ix++) {
776 if (k != 0 &&
777 le32_to_cpu(ix->ei_block) <= le32_to_cpu(ix[-1].ei_block)) {
778 printk(KERN_DEBUG "k=%d, ix=0x%p, "
779 "first=0x%p\n", k,
780 ix, EXT_FIRST_INDEX(eh));
781 printk(KERN_DEBUG "%u <= %u\n",
782 le32_to_cpu(ix->ei_block),
783 le32_to_cpu(ix[-1].ei_block));
784 }
785 BUG_ON(k && le32_to_cpu(ix->ei_block)
786 <= le32_to_cpu(ix[-1].ei_block));
787 if (block < le32_to_cpu(ix->ei_block))
788 break;
789 chix = ix;
790 }
791 BUG_ON(chix != path->p_idx);
792 }
793#endif
794
795}
796
797/*
798 * ext4_ext_binsearch:
799 * binary search for closest extent of the given block
800 * the header must be checked before calling this
801 */
802static void
803ext4_ext_binsearch(struct inode *inode,
804 struct ext4_ext_path *path, ext4_lblk_t block)
805{
806 struct ext4_extent_header *eh = path->p_hdr;
807 struct ext4_extent *r, *l, *m;
808
809 if (eh->eh_entries == 0) {
810 /*
811 * this leaf is empty:
812 * we get such a leaf in split/add case
813 */
814 return;
815 }
816
817 ext_debug("binsearch for %u: ", block);
818
819 l = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh) + 1;
820 r = EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh);
821
822 while (l <= r) {
823 m = l + (r - l) / 2;
824 if (block < le32_to_cpu(m->ee_block))
825 r = m - 1;
826 else
827 l = m + 1;
828 ext_debug("%p(%u):%p(%u):%p(%u) ", l, le32_to_cpu(l->ee_block),
829 m, le32_to_cpu(m->ee_block),
830 r, le32_to_cpu(r->ee_block));
831 }
832
833 path->p_ext = l - 1;
834 ext_debug(" -> %d:%llu:[%d]%d ",
835 le32_to_cpu(path->p_ext->ee_block),
836 ext4_ext_pblock(path->p_ext),
837 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(path->p_ext),
838 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(path->p_ext));
839
840#ifdef CHECK_BINSEARCH
841 {
842 struct ext4_extent *chex, *ex;
843 int k;
844
845 chex = ex = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh);
846 for (k = 0; k < le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries); k++, ex++) {
847 BUG_ON(k && le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)
848 <= le32_to_cpu(ex[-1].ee_block));
849 if (block < le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block))
850 break;
851 chex = ex;
852 }
853 BUG_ON(chex != path->p_ext);
854 }
855#endif
856
857}
858
859int ext4_ext_tree_init(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode)
860{
861 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
862
863 eh = ext_inode_hdr(inode);
864 eh->eh_depth = 0;
865 eh->eh_entries = 0;
866 eh->eh_magic = EXT4_EXT_MAGIC;
867 eh->eh_max = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_space_root(inode, 0));
868 ext4_mark_inode_dirty(handle, inode);
869 return 0;
870}
871
872struct ext4_ext_path *
873ext4_find_extent(struct inode *inode, ext4_lblk_t block,
874 struct ext4_ext_path **orig_path, int flags)
875{
876 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
877 struct buffer_head *bh;
878 struct ext4_ext_path *path = orig_path ? *orig_path : NULL;
879 short int depth, i, ppos = 0;
880 int ret;
881
882 eh = ext_inode_hdr(inode);
883 depth = ext_depth(inode);
884 if (depth < 0 || depth > EXT4_MAX_EXTENT_DEPTH) {
885 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "inode has invalid extent depth: %d",
886 depth);
887 ret = -EFSCORRUPTED;
888 goto err;
889 }
890
891 if (path) {
892 ext4_ext_drop_refs(path);
893 if (depth > path[0].p_maxdepth) {
894 kfree(path);
895 *orig_path = path = NULL;
896 }
897 }
898 if (!path) {
899 /* account possible depth increase */
900 path = kzalloc(sizeof(struct ext4_ext_path) * (depth + 2),
901 GFP_NOFS);
902 if (unlikely(!path))
903 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
904 path[0].p_maxdepth = depth + 1;
905 }
906 path[0].p_hdr = eh;
907 path[0].p_bh = NULL;
908
909 i = depth;
910 /* walk through the tree */
911 while (i) {
912 ext_debug("depth %d: num %d, max %d\n",
913 ppos, le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries), le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_max));
914
915 ext4_ext_binsearch_idx(inode, path + ppos, block);
916 path[ppos].p_block = ext4_idx_pblock(path[ppos].p_idx);
917 path[ppos].p_depth = i;
918 path[ppos].p_ext = NULL;
919
920 bh = read_extent_tree_block(inode, path[ppos].p_block, --i,
921 flags);
922 if (IS_ERR(bh)) {
923 ret = PTR_ERR(bh);
924 goto err;
925 }
926
927 eh = ext_block_hdr(bh);
928 ppos++;
929 path[ppos].p_bh = bh;
930 path[ppos].p_hdr = eh;
931 }
932
933 path[ppos].p_depth = i;
934 path[ppos].p_ext = NULL;
935 path[ppos].p_idx = NULL;
936
937 /* find extent */
938 ext4_ext_binsearch(inode, path + ppos, block);
939 /* if not an empty leaf */
940 if (path[ppos].p_ext)
941 path[ppos].p_block = ext4_ext_pblock(path[ppos].p_ext);
942
943 ext4_ext_show_path(inode, path);
944
945 return path;
946
947err:
948 ext4_ext_drop_refs(path);
949 kfree(path);
950 if (orig_path)
951 *orig_path = NULL;
952 return ERR_PTR(ret);
953}
954
955/*
956 * ext4_ext_insert_index:
957 * insert new index [@logical;@ptr] into the block at @curp;
958 * check where to insert: before @curp or after @curp
959 */
960static int ext4_ext_insert_index(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
961 struct ext4_ext_path *curp,
962 int logical, ext4_fsblk_t ptr)
963{
964 struct ext4_extent_idx *ix;
965 int len, err;
966
967 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, curp);
968 if (err)
969 return err;
970
971 if (unlikely(logical == le32_to_cpu(curp->p_idx->ei_block))) {
972 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
973 "logical %d == ei_block %d!",
974 logical, le32_to_cpu(curp->p_idx->ei_block));
975 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
976 }
977
978 if (unlikely(le16_to_cpu(curp->p_hdr->eh_entries)
979 >= le16_to_cpu(curp->p_hdr->eh_max))) {
980 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
981 "eh_entries %d >= eh_max %d!",
982 le16_to_cpu(curp->p_hdr->eh_entries),
983 le16_to_cpu(curp->p_hdr->eh_max));
984 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
985 }
986
987 if (logical > le32_to_cpu(curp->p_idx->ei_block)) {
988 /* insert after */
989 ext_debug("insert new index %d after: %llu\n", logical, ptr);
990 ix = curp->p_idx + 1;
991 } else {
992 /* insert before */
993 ext_debug("insert new index %d before: %llu\n", logical, ptr);
994 ix = curp->p_idx;
995 }
996
997 len = EXT_LAST_INDEX(curp->p_hdr) - ix + 1;
998 BUG_ON(len < 0);
999 if (len > 0) {
1000 ext_debug("insert new index %d: "
1001 "move %d indices from 0x%p to 0x%p\n",
1002 logical, len, ix, ix + 1);
1003 memmove(ix + 1, ix, len * sizeof(struct ext4_extent_idx));
1004 }
1005
1006 if (unlikely(ix > EXT_MAX_INDEX(curp->p_hdr))) {
1007 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "ix > EXT_MAX_INDEX!");
1008 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1009 }
1010
1011 ix->ei_block = cpu_to_le32(logical);
1012 ext4_idx_store_pblock(ix, ptr);
1013 le16_add_cpu(&curp->p_hdr->eh_entries, 1);
1014
1015 if (unlikely(ix > EXT_LAST_INDEX(curp->p_hdr))) {
1016 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "ix > EXT_LAST_INDEX!");
1017 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1018 }
1019
1020 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, curp);
1021 ext4_std_error(inode->i_sb, err);
1022
1023 return err;
1024}
1025
1026/*
1027 * ext4_ext_split:
1028 * inserts new subtree into the path, using free index entry
1029 * at depth @at:
1030 * - allocates all needed blocks (new leaf and all intermediate index blocks)
1031 * - makes decision where to split
1032 * - moves remaining extents and index entries (right to the split point)
1033 * into the newly allocated blocks
1034 * - initializes subtree
1035 */
1036static int ext4_ext_split(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
1037 unsigned int flags,
1038 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
1039 struct ext4_extent *newext, int at)
1040{
1041 struct buffer_head *bh = NULL;
1042 int depth = ext_depth(inode);
1043 struct ext4_extent_header *neh;
1044 struct ext4_extent_idx *fidx;
1045 int i = at, k, m, a;
1046 ext4_fsblk_t newblock, oldblock;
1047 __le32 border;
1048 ext4_fsblk_t *ablocks = NULL; /* array of allocated blocks */
1049 int err = 0;
1050
1051 /* make decision: where to split? */
1052 /* FIXME: now decision is simplest: at current extent */
1053
1054 /* if current leaf will be split, then we should use
1055 * border from split point */
1056 if (unlikely(path[depth].p_ext > EXT_MAX_EXTENT(path[depth].p_hdr))) {
1057 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "p_ext > EXT_MAX_EXTENT!");
1058 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1059 }
1060 if (path[depth].p_ext != EXT_MAX_EXTENT(path[depth].p_hdr)) {
1061 border = path[depth].p_ext[1].ee_block;
1062 ext_debug("leaf will be split."
1063 " next leaf starts at %d\n",
1064 le32_to_cpu(border));
1065 } else {
1066 border = newext->ee_block;
1067 ext_debug("leaf will be added."
1068 " next leaf starts at %d\n",
1069 le32_to_cpu(border));
1070 }
1071
1072 /*
1073 * If error occurs, then we break processing
1074 * and mark filesystem read-only. index won't
1075 * be inserted and tree will be in consistent
1076 * state. Next mount will repair buffers too.
1077 */
1078
1079 /*
1080 * Get array to track all allocated blocks.
1081 * We need this to handle errors and free blocks
1082 * upon them.
1083 */
1084 ablocks = kzalloc(sizeof(ext4_fsblk_t) * depth, GFP_NOFS);
1085 if (!ablocks)
1086 return -ENOMEM;
1087
1088 /* allocate all needed blocks */
1089 ext_debug("allocate %d blocks for indexes/leaf\n", depth - at);
1090 for (a = 0; a < depth - at; a++) {
1091 newblock = ext4_ext_new_meta_block(handle, inode, path,
1092 newext, &err, flags);
1093 if (newblock == 0)
1094 goto cleanup;
1095 ablocks[a] = newblock;
1096 }
1097
1098 /* initialize new leaf */
1099 newblock = ablocks[--a];
1100 if (unlikely(newblock == 0)) {
1101 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "newblock == 0!");
1102 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
1103 goto cleanup;
1104 }
1105 bh = sb_getblk_gfp(inode->i_sb, newblock, __GFP_MOVABLE | GFP_NOFS);
1106 if (unlikely(!bh)) {
1107 err = -ENOMEM;
1108 goto cleanup;
1109 }
1110 lock_buffer(bh);
1111
1112 err = ext4_journal_get_create_access(handle, bh);
1113 if (err)
1114 goto cleanup;
1115
1116 neh = ext_block_hdr(bh);
1117 neh->eh_entries = 0;
1118 neh->eh_max = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_space_block(inode, 0));
1119 neh->eh_magic = EXT4_EXT_MAGIC;
1120 neh->eh_depth = 0;
1121
1122 /* move remainder of path[depth] to the new leaf */
1123 if (unlikely(path[depth].p_hdr->eh_entries !=
1124 path[depth].p_hdr->eh_max)) {
1125 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "eh_entries %d != eh_max %d!",
1126 path[depth].p_hdr->eh_entries,
1127 path[depth].p_hdr->eh_max);
1128 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
1129 goto cleanup;
1130 }
1131 /* start copy from next extent */
1132 m = EXT_MAX_EXTENT(path[depth].p_hdr) - path[depth].p_ext++;
1133 ext4_ext_show_move(inode, path, newblock, depth);
1134 if (m) {
1135 struct ext4_extent *ex;
1136 ex = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(neh);
1137 memmove(ex, path[depth].p_ext, sizeof(struct ext4_extent) * m);
1138 le16_add_cpu(&neh->eh_entries, m);
1139 }
1140
1141 ext4_extent_block_csum_set(inode, neh);
1142 set_buffer_uptodate(bh);
1143 unlock_buffer(bh);
1144
1145 err = ext4_handle_dirty_metadata(handle, inode, bh);
1146 if (err)
1147 goto cleanup;
1148 brelse(bh);
1149 bh = NULL;
1150
1151 /* correct old leaf */
1152 if (m) {
1153 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + depth);
1154 if (err)
1155 goto cleanup;
1156 le16_add_cpu(&path[depth].p_hdr->eh_entries, -m);
1157 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + depth);
1158 if (err)
1159 goto cleanup;
1160
1161 }
1162
1163 /* create intermediate indexes */
1164 k = depth - at - 1;
1165 if (unlikely(k < 0)) {
1166 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "k %d < 0!", k);
1167 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
1168 goto cleanup;
1169 }
1170 if (k)
1171 ext_debug("create %d intermediate indices\n", k);
1172 /* insert new index into current index block */
1173 /* current depth stored in i var */
1174 i = depth - 1;
1175 while (k--) {
1176 oldblock = newblock;
1177 newblock = ablocks[--a];
1178 bh = sb_getblk(inode->i_sb, newblock);
1179 if (unlikely(!bh)) {
1180 err = -ENOMEM;
1181 goto cleanup;
1182 }
1183 lock_buffer(bh);
1184
1185 err = ext4_journal_get_create_access(handle, bh);
1186 if (err)
1187 goto cleanup;
1188
1189 neh = ext_block_hdr(bh);
1190 neh->eh_entries = cpu_to_le16(1);
1191 neh->eh_magic = EXT4_EXT_MAGIC;
1192 neh->eh_max = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_space_block_idx(inode, 0));
1193 neh->eh_depth = cpu_to_le16(depth - i);
1194 fidx = EXT_FIRST_INDEX(neh);
1195 fidx->ei_block = border;
1196 ext4_idx_store_pblock(fidx, oldblock);
1197
1198 ext_debug("int.index at %d (block %llu): %u -> %llu\n",
1199 i, newblock, le32_to_cpu(border), oldblock);
1200
1201 /* move remainder of path[i] to the new index block */
1202 if (unlikely(EXT_MAX_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr) !=
1203 EXT_LAST_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr))) {
1204 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
1205 "EXT_MAX_INDEX != EXT_LAST_INDEX ee_block %d!",
1206 le32_to_cpu(path[i].p_ext->ee_block));
1207 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
1208 goto cleanup;
1209 }
1210 /* start copy indexes */
1211 m = EXT_MAX_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr) - path[i].p_idx++;
1212 ext_debug("cur 0x%p, last 0x%p\n", path[i].p_idx,
1213 EXT_MAX_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr));
1214 ext4_ext_show_move(inode, path, newblock, i);
1215 if (m) {
1216 memmove(++fidx, path[i].p_idx,
1217 sizeof(struct ext4_extent_idx) * m);
1218 le16_add_cpu(&neh->eh_entries, m);
1219 }
1220 ext4_extent_block_csum_set(inode, neh);
1221 set_buffer_uptodate(bh);
1222 unlock_buffer(bh);
1223
1224 err = ext4_handle_dirty_metadata(handle, inode, bh);
1225 if (err)
1226 goto cleanup;
1227 brelse(bh);
1228 bh = NULL;
1229
1230 /* correct old index */
1231 if (m) {
1232 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + i);
1233 if (err)
1234 goto cleanup;
1235 le16_add_cpu(&path[i].p_hdr->eh_entries, -m);
1236 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + i);
1237 if (err)
1238 goto cleanup;
1239 }
1240
1241 i--;
1242 }
1243
1244 /* insert new index */
1245 err = ext4_ext_insert_index(handle, inode, path + at,
1246 le32_to_cpu(border), newblock);
1247
1248cleanup:
1249 if (bh) {
1250 if (buffer_locked(bh))
1251 unlock_buffer(bh);
1252 brelse(bh);
1253 }
1254
1255 if (err) {
1256 /* free all allocated blocks in error case */
1257 for (i = 0; i < depth; i++) {
1258 if (!ablocks[i])
1259 continue;
1260 ext4_free_blocks(handle, inode, NULL, ablocks[i], 1,
1261 EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_METADATA);
1262 }
1263 }
1264 kfree(ablocks);
1265
1266 return err;
1267}
1268
1269/*
1270 * ext4_ext_grow_indepth:
1271 * implements tree growing procedure:
1272 * - allocates new block
1273 * - moves top-level data (index block or leaf) into the new block
1274 * - initializes new top-level, creating index that points to the
1275 * just created block
1276 */
1277static int ext4_ext_grow_indepth(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
1278 unsigned int flags)
1279{
1280 struct ext4_extent_header *neh;
1281 struct buffer_head *bh;
1282 ext4_fsblk_t newblock, goal = 0;
1283 struct ext4_super_block *es = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb)->s_es;
1284 int err = 0;
1285
1286 /* Try to prepend new index to old one */
1287 if (ext_depth(inode))
1288 goal = ext4_idx_pblock(EXT_FIRST_INDEX(ext_inode_hdr(inode)));
1289 if (goal > le32_to_cpu(es->s_first_data_block)) {
1290 flags |= EXT4_MB_HINT_TRY_GOAL;
1291 goal--;
1292 } else
1293 goal = ext4_inode_to_goal_block(inode);
1294 newblock = ext4_new_meta_blocks(handle, inode, goal, flags,
1295 NULL, &err);
1296 if (newblock == 0)
1297 return err;
1298
1299 bh = sb_getblk_gfp(inode->i_sb, newblock, __GFP_MOVABLE | GFP_NOFS);
1300 if (unlikely(!bh))
1301 return -ENOMEM;
1302 lock_buffer(bh);
1303
1304 err = ext4_journal_get_create_access(handle, bh);
1305 if (err) {
1306 unlock_buffer(bh);
1307 goto out;
1308 }
1309
1310 /* move top-level index/leaf into new block */
1311 memmove(bh->b_data, EXT4_I(inode)->i_data,
1312 sizeof(EXT4_I(inode)->i_data));
1313
1314 /* set size of new block */
1315 neh = ext_block_hdr(bh);
1316 /* old root could have indexes or leaves
1317 * so calculate e_max right way */
1318 if (ext_depth(inode))
1319 neh->eh_max = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_space_block_idx(inode, 0));
1320 else
1321 neh->eh_max = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_space_block(inode, 0));
1322 neh->eh_magic = EXT4_EXT_MAGIC;
1323 ext4_extent_block_csum_set(inode, neh);
1324 set_buffer_uptodate(bh);
1325 unlock_buffer(bh);
1326
1327 err = ext4_handle_dirty_metadata(handle, inode, bh);
1328 if (err)
1329 goto out;
1330
1331 /* Update top-level index: num,max,pointer */
1332 neh = ext_inode_hdr(inode);
1333 neh->eh_entries = cpu_to_le16(1);
1334 ext4_idx_store_pblock(EXT_FIRST_INDEX(neh), newblock);
1335 if (neh->eh_depth == 0) {
1336 /* Root extent block becomes index block */
1337 neh->eh_max = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_space_root_idx(inode, 0));
1338 EXT_FIRST_INDEX(neh)->ei_block =
1339 EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(neh)->ee_block;
1340 }
1341 ext_debug("new root: num %d(%d), lblock %d, ptr %llu\n",
1342 le16_to_cpu(neh->eh_entries), le16_to_cpu(neh->eh_max),
1343 le32_to_cpu(EXT_FIRST_INDEX(neh)->ei_block),
1344 ext4_idx_pblock(EXT_FIRST_INDEX(neh)));
1345
1346 le16_add_cpu(&neh->eh_depth, 1);
1347 ext4_mark_inode_dirty(handle, inode);
1348out:
1349 brelse(bh);
1350
1351 return err;
1352}
1353
1354/*
1355 * ext4_ext_create_new_leaf:
1356 * finds empty index and adds new leaf.
1357 * if no free index is found, then it requests in-depth growing.
1358 */
1359static int ext4_ext_create_new_leaf(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
1360 unsigned int mb_flags,
1361 unsigned int gb_flags,
1362 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath,
1363 struct ext4_extent *newext)
1364{
1365 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
1366 struct ext4_ext_path *curp;
1367 int depth, i, err = 0;
1368
1369repeat:
1370 i = depth = ext_depth(inode);
1371
1372 /* walk up to the tree and look for free index entry */
1373 curp = path + depth;
1374 while (i > 0 && !EXT_HAS_FREE_INDEX(curp)) {
1375 i--;
1376 curp--;
1377 }
1378
1379 /* we use already allocated block for index block,
1380 * so subsequent data blocks should be contiguous */
1381 if (EXT_HAS_FREE_INDEX(curp)) {
1382 /* if we found index with free entry, then use that
1383 * entry: create all needed subtree and add new leaf */
1384 err = ext4_ext_split(handle, inode, mb_flags, path, newext, i);
1385 if (err)
1386 goto out;
1387
1388 /* refill path */
1389 path = ext4_find_extent(inode,
1390 (ext4_lblk_t)le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block),
1391 ppath, gb_flags);
1392 if (IS_ERR(path))
1393 err = PTR_ERR(path);
1394 } else {
1395 /* tree is full, time to grow in depth */
1396 err = ext4_ext_grow_indepth(handle, inode, mb_flags);
1397 if (err)
1398 goto out;
1399
1400 /* refill path */
1401 path = ext4_find_extent(inode,
1402 (ext4_lblk_t)le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block),
1403 ppath, gb_flags);
1404 if (IS_ERR(path)) {
1405 err = PTR_ERR(path);
1406 goto out;
1407 }
1408
1409 /*
1410 * only first (depth 0 -> 1) produces free space;
1411 * in all other cases we have to split the grown tree
1412 */
1413 depth = ext_depth(inode);
1414 if (path[depth].p_hdr->eh_entries == path[depth].p_hdr->eh_max) {
1415 /* now we need to split */
1416 goto repeat;
1417 }
1418 }
1419
1420out:
1421 return err;
1422}
1423
1424/*
1425 * search the closest allocated block to the left for *logical
1426 * and returns it at @logical + it's physical address at @phys
1427 * if *logical is the smallest allocated block, the function
1428 * returns 0 at @phys
1429 * return value contains 0 (success) or error code
1430 */
1431static int ext4_ext_search_left(struct inode *inode,
1432 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
1433 ext4_lblk_t *logical, ext4_fsblk_t *phys)
1434{
1435 struct ext4_extent_idx *ix;
1436 struct ext4_extent *ex;
1437 int depth, ee_len;
1438
1439 if (unlikely(path == NULL)) {
1440 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "path == NULL *logical %d!", *logical);
1441 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1442 }
1443 depth = path->p_depth;
1444 *phys = 0;
1445
1446 if (depth == 0 && path->p_ext == NULL)
1447 return 0;
1448
1449 /* usually extent in the path covers blocks smaller
1450 * then *logical, but it can be that extent is the
1451 * first one in the file */
1452
1453 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
1454 ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
1455 if (*logical < le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)) {
1456 if (unlikely(EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(path[depth].p_hdr) != ex)) {
1457 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
1458 "EXT_FIRST_EXTENT != ex *logical %d ee_block %d!",
1459 *logical, le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block));
1460 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1461 }
1462 while (--depth >= 0) {
1463 ix = path[depth].p_idx;
1464 if (unlikely(ix != EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path[depth].p_hdr))) {
1465 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
1466 "ix (%d) != EXT_FIRST_INDEX (%d) (depth %d)!",
1467 ix != NULL ? le32_to_cpu(ix->ei_block) : 0,
1468 EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path[depth].p_hdr) != NULL ?
1469 le32_to_cpu(EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path[depth].p_hdr)->ei_block) : 0,
1470 depth);
1471 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1472 }
1473 }
1474 return 0;
1475 }
1476
1477 if (unlikely(*logical < (le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) + ee_len))) {
1478 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
1479 "logical %d < ee_block %d + ee_len %d!",
1480 *logical, le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block), ee_len);
1481 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1482 }
1483
1484 *logical = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) + ee_len - 1;
1485 *phys = ext4_ext_pblock(ex) + ee_len - 1;
1486 return 0;
1487}
1488
1489/*
1490 * search the closest allocated block to the right for *logical
1491 * and returns it at @logical + it's physical address at @phys
1492 * if *logical is the largest allocated block, the function
1493 * returns 0 at @phys
1494 * return value contains 0 (success) or error code
1495 */
1496static int ext4_ext_search_right(struct inode *inode,
1497 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
1498 ext4_lblk_t *logical, ext4_fsblk_t *phys,
1499 struct ext4_extent **ret_ex)
1500{
1501 struct buffer_head *bh = NULL;
1502 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
1503 struct ext4_extent_idx *ix;
1504 struct ext4_extent *ex;
1505 ext4_fsblk_t block;
1506 int depth; /* Note, NOT eh_depth; depth from top of tree */
1507 int ee_len;
1508
1509 if (unlikely(path == NULL)) {
1510 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "path == NULL *logical %d!", *logical);
1511 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1512 }
1513 depth = path->p_depth;
1514 *phys = 0;
1515
1516 if (depth == 0 && path->p_ext == NULL)
1517 return 0;
1518
1519 /* usually extent in the path covers blocks smaller
1520 * then *logical, but it can be that extent is the
1521 * first one in the file */
1522
1523 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
1524 ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
1525 if (*logical < le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)) {
1526 if (unlikely(EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(path[depth].p_hdr) != ex)) {
1527 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
1528 "first_extent(path[%d].p_hdr) != ex",
1529 depth);
1530 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1531 }
1532 while (--depth >= 0) {
1533 ix = path[depth].p_idx;
1534 if (unlikely(ix != EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path[depth].p_hdr))) {
1535 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
1536 "ix != EXT_FIRST_INDEX *logical %d!",
1537 *logical);
1538 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1539 }
1540 }
1541 goto found_extent;
1542 }
1543
1544 if (unlikely(*logical < (le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) + ee_len))) {
1545 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
1546 "logical %d < ee_block %d + ee_len %d!",
1547 *logical, le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block), ee_len);
1548 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1549 }
1550
1551 if (ex != EXT_LAST_EXTENT(path[depth].p_hdr)) {
1552 /* next allocated block in this leaf */
1553 ex++;
1554 goto found_extent;
1555 }
1556
1557 /* go up and search for index to the right */
1558 while (--depth >= 0) {
1559 ix = path[depth].p_idx;
1560 if (ix != EXT_LAST_INDEX(path[depth].p_hdr))
1561 goto got_index;
1562 }
1563
1564 /* we've gone up to the root and found no index to the right */
1565 return 0;
1566
1567got_index:
1568 /* we've found index to the right, let's
1569 * follow it and find the closest allocated
1570 * block to the right */
1571 ix++;
1572 block = ext4_idx_pblock(ix);
1573 while (++depth < path->p_depth) {
1574 /* subtract from p_depth to get proper eh_depth */
1575 bh = read_extent_tree_block(inode, block,
1576 path->p_depth - depth, 0);
1577 if (IS_ERR(bh))
1578 return PTR_ERR(bh);
1579 eh = ext_block_hdr(bh);
1580 ix = EXT_FIRST_INDEX(eh);
1581 block = ext4_idx_pblock(ix);
1582 put_bh(bh);
1583 }
1584
1585 bh = read_extent_tree_block(inode, block, path->p_depth - depth, 0);
1586 if (IS_ERR(bh))
1587 return PTR_ERR(bh);
1588 eh = ext_block_hdr(bh);
1589 ex = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh);
1590found_extent:
1591 *logical = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
1592 *phys = ext4_ext_pblock(ex);
1593 *ret_ex = ex;
1594 if (bh)
1595 put_bh(bh);
1596 return 0;
1597}
1598
1599/*
1600 * ext4_ext_next_allocated_block:
1601 * returns allocated block in subsequent extent or EXT_MAX_BLOCKS.
1602 * NOTE: it considers block number from index entry as
1603 * allocated block. Thus, index entries have to be consistent
1604 * with leaves.
1605 */
1606ext4_lblk_t
1607ext4_ext_next_allocated_block(struct ext4_ext_path *path)
1608{
1609 int depth;
1610
1611 BUG_ON(path == NULL);
1612 depth = path->p_depth;
1613
1614 if (depth == 0 && path->p_ext == NULL)
1615 return EXT_MAX_BLOCKS;
1616
1617 while (depth >= 0) {
1618 if (depth == path->p_depth) {
1619 /* leaf */
1620 if (path[depth].p_ext &&
1621 path[depth].p_ext !=
1622 EXT_LAST_EXTENT(path[depth].p_hdr))
1623 return le32_to_cpu(path[depth].p_ext[1].ee_block);
1624 } else {
1625 /* index */
1626 if (path[depth].p_idx !=
1627 EXT_LAST_INDEX(path[depth].p_hdr))
1628 return le32_to_cpu(path[depth].p_idx[1].ei_block);
1629 }
1630 depth--;
1631 }
1632
1633 return EXT_MAX_BLOCKS;
1634}
1635
1636/*
1637 * ext4_ext_next_leaf_block:
1638 * returns first allocated block from next leaf or EXT_MAX_BLOCKS
1639 */
1640static ext4_lblk_t ext4_ext_next_leaf_block(struct ext4_ext_path *path)
1641{
1642 int depth;
1643
1644 BUG_ON(path == NULL);
1645 depth = path->p_depth;
1646
1647 /* zero-tree has no leaf blocks at all */
1648 if (depth == 0)
1649 return EXT_MAX_BLOCKS;
1650
1651 /* go to index block */
1652 depth--;
1653
1654 while (depth >= 0) {
1655 if (path[depth].p_idx !=
1656 EXT_LAST_INDEX(path[depth].p_hdr))
1657 return (ext4_lblk_t)
1658 le32_to_cpu(path[depth].p_idx[1].ei_block);
1659 depth--;
1660 }
1661
1662 return EXT_MAX_BLOCKS;
1663}
1664
1665/*
1666 * ext4_ext_correct_indexes:
1667 * if leaf gets modified and modified extent is first in the leaf,
1668 * then we have to correct all indexes above.
1669 * TODO: do we need to correct tree in all cases?
1670 */
1671static int ext4_ext_correct_indexes(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
1672 struct ext4_ext_path *path)
1673{
1674 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
1675 int depth = ext_depth(inode);
1676 struct ext4_extent *ex;
1677 __le32 border;
1678 int k, err = 0;
1679
1680 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
1681 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
1682
1683 if (unlikely(ex == NULL || eh == NULL)) {
1684 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
1685 "ex %p == NULL or eh %p == NULL", ex, eh);
1686 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1687 }
1688
1689 if (depth == 0) {
1690 /* there is no tree at all */
1691 return 0;
1692 }
1693
1694 if (ex != EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh)) {
1695 /* we correct tree if first leaf got modified only */
1696 return 0;
1697 }
1698
1699 /*
1700 * TODO: we need correction if border is smaller than current one
1701 */
1702 k = depth - 1;
1703 border = path[depth].p_ext->ee_block;
1704 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + k);
1705 if (err)
1706 return err;
1707 path[k].p_idx->ei_block = border;
1708 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + k);
1709 if (err)
1710 return err;
1711
1712 while (k--) {
1713 /* change all left-side indexes */
1714 if (path[k+1].p_idx != EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path[k+1].p_hdr))
1715 break;
1716 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + k);
1717 if (err)
1718 break;
1719 path[k].p_idx->ei_block = border;
1720 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + k);
1721 if (err)
1722 break;
1723 }
1724
1725 return err;
1726}
1727
1728int
1729ext4_can_extents_be_merged(struct inode *inode, struct ext4_extent *ex1,
1730 struct ext4_extent *ex2)
1731{
1732 unsigned short ext1_ee_len, ext2_ee_len;
1733
1734 if (ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex1) != ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex2))
1735 return 0;
1736
1737 ext1_ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex1);
1738 ext2_ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex2);
1739
1740 if (le32_to_cpu(ex1->ee_block) + ext1_ee_len !=
1741 le32_to_cpu(ex2->ee_block))
1742 return 0;
1743
1744 /*
1745 * To allow future support for preallocated extents to be added
1746 * as an RO_COMPAT feature, refuse to merge to extents if
1747 * this can result in the top bit of ee_len being set.
1748 */
1749 if (ext1_ee_len + ext2_ee_len > EXT_INIT_MAX_LEN)
1750 return 0;
1751 /*
1752 * The check for IO to unwritten extent is somewhat racy as we
1753 * increment i_unwritten / set EXT4_STATE_DIO_UNWRITTEN only after
1754 * dropping i_data_sem. But reserved blocks should save us in that
1755 * case.
1756 */
1757 if (ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex1) &&
1758 (ext4_test_inode_state(inode, EXT4_STATE_DIO_UNWRITTEN) ||
1759 atomic_read(&EXT4_I(inode)->i_unwritten) ||
1760 (ext1_ee_len + ext2_ee_len > EXT_UNWRITTEN_MAX_LEN)))
1761 return 0;
1762#ifdef AGGRESSIVE_TEST
1763 if (ext1_ee_len >= 4)
1764 return 0;
1765#endif
1766
1767 if (ext4_ext_pblock(ex1) + ext1_ee_len == ext4_ext_pblock(ex2))
1768 return 1;
1769 return 0;
1770}
1771
1772/*
1773 * This function tries to merge the "ex" extent to the next extent in the tree.
1774 * It always tries to merge towards right. If you want to merge towards
1775 * left, pass "ex - 1" as argument instead of "ex".
1776 * Returns 0 if the extents (ex and ex+1) were _not_ merged and returns
1777 * 1 if they got merged.
1778 */
1779static int ext4_ext_try_to_merge_right(struct inode *inode,
1780 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
1781 struct ext4_extent *ex)
1782{
1783 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
1784 unsigned int depth, len;
1785 int merge_done = 0, unwritten;
1786
1787 depth = ext_depth(inode);
1788 BUG_ON(path[depth].p_hdr == NULL);
1789 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
1790
1791 while (ex < EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh)) {
1792 if (!ext4_can_extents_be_merged(inode, ex, ex + 1))
1793 break;
1794 /* merge with next extent! */
1795 unwritten = ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex);
1796 ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex)
1797 + ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex + 1));
1798 if (unwritten)
1799 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex);
1800
1801 if (ex + 1 < EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh)) {
1802 len = (EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh) - ex - 1)
1803 * sizeof(struct ext4_extent);
1804 memmove(ex + 1, ex + 2, len);
1805 }
1806 le16_add_cpu(&eh->eh_entries, -1);
1807 merge_done = 1;
1808 WARN_ON(eh->eh_entries == 0);
1809 if (!eh->eh_entries)
1810 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "eh->eh_entries = 0!");
1811 }
1812
1813 return merge_done;
1814}
1815
1816/*
1817 * This function does a very simple check to see if we can collapse
1818 * an extent tree with a single extent tree leaf block into the inode.
1819 */
1820static void ext4_ext_try_to_merge_up(handle_t *handle,
1821 struct inode *inode,
1822 struct ext4_ext_path *path)
1823{
1824 size_t s;
1825 unsigned max_root = ext4_ext_space_root(inode, 0);
1826 ext4_fsblk_t blk;
1827
1828 if ((path[0].p_depth != 1) ||
1829 (le16_to_cpu(path[0].p_hdr->eh_entries) != 1) ||
1830 (le16_to_cpu(path[1].p_hdr->eh_entries) > max_root))
1831 return;
1832
1833 /*
1834 * We need to modify the block allocation bitmap and the block
1835 * group descriptor to release the extent tree block. If we
1836 * can't get the journal credits, give up.
1837 */
1838 if (ext4_journal_extend(handle, 2))
1839 return;
1840
1841 /*
1842 * Copy the extent data up to the inode
1843 */
1844 blk = ext4_idx_pblock(path[0].p_idx);
1845 s = le16_to_cpu(path[1].p_hdr->eh_entries) *
1846 sizeof(struct ext4_extent_idx);
1847 s += sizeof(struct ext4_extent_header);
1848
1849 path[1].p_maxdepth = path[0].p_maxdepth;
1850 memcpy(path[0].p_hdr, path[1].p_hdr, s);
1851 path[0].p_depth = 0;
1852 path[0].p_ext = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(path[0].p_hdr) +
1853 (path[1].p_ext - EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(path[1].p_hdr));
1854 path[0].p_hdr->eh_max = cpu_to_le16(max_root);
1855
1856 brelse(path[1].p_bh);
1857 ext4_free_blocks(handle, inode, NULL, blk, 1,
1858 EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_METADATA | EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_FORGET);
1859}
1860
1861/*
1862 * This function tries to merge the @ex extent to neighbours in the tree.
1863 * return 1 if merge left else 0.
1864 */
1865static void ext4_ext_try_to_merge(handle_t *handle,
1866 struct inode *inode,
1867 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
1868 struct ext4_extent *ex) {
1869 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
1870 unsigned int depth;
1871 int merge_done = 0;
1872
1873 depth = ext_depth(inode);
1874 BUG_ON(path[depth].p_hdr == NULL);
1875 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
1876
1877 if (ex > EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh))
1878 merge_done = ext4_ext_try_to_merge_right(inode, path, ex - 1);
1879
1880 if (!merge_done)
1881 (void) ext4_ext_try_to_merge_right(inode, path, ex);
1882
1883 ext4_ext_try_to_merge_up(handle, inode, path);
1884}
1885
1886/*
1887 * check if a portion of the "newext" extent overlaps with an
1888 * existing extent.
1889 *
1890 * If there is an overlap discovered, it updates the length of the newext
1891 * such that there will be no overlap, and then returns 1.
1892 * If there is no overlap found, it returns 0.
1893 */
1894static unsigned int ext4_ext_check_overlap(struct ext4_sb_info *sbi,
1895 struct inode *inode,
1896 struct ext4_extent *newext,
1897 struct ext4_ext_path *path)
1898{
1899 ext4_lblk_t b1, b2;
1900 unsigned int depth, len1;
1901 unsigned int ret = 0;
1902
1903 b1 = le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block);
1904 len1 = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext);
1905 depth = ext_depth(inode);
1906 if (!path[depth].p_ext)
1907 goto out;
1908 b2 = EXT4_LBLK_CMASK(sbi, le32_to_cpu(path[depth].p_ext->ee_block));
1909
1910 /*
1911 * get the next allocated block if the extent in the path
1912 * is before the requested block(s)
1913 */
1914 if (b2 < b1) {
1915 b2 = ext4_ext_next_allocated_block(path);
1916 if (b2 == EXT_MAX_BLOCKS)
1917 goto out;
1918 b2 = EXT4_LBLK_CMASK(sbi, b2);
1919 }
1920
1921 /* check for wrap through zero on extent logical start block*/
1922 if (b1 + len1 < b1) {
1923 len1 = EXT_MAX_BLOCKS - b1;
1924 newext->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(len1);
1925 ret = 1;
1926 }
1927
1928 /* check for overlap */
1929 if (b1 + len1 > b2) {
1930 newext->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(b2 - b1);
1931 ret = 1;
1932 }
1933out:
1934 return ret;
1935}
1936
1937/*
1938 * ext4_ext_insert_extent:
1939 * tries to merge requsted extent into the existing extent or
1940 * inserts requested extent as new one into the tree,
1941 * creating new leaf in the no-space case.
1942 */
1943int ext4_ext_insert_extent(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
1944 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath,
1945 struct ext4_extent *newext, int gb_flags)
1946{
1947 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
1948 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
1949 struct ext4_extent *ex, *fex;
1950 struct ext4_extent *nearex; /* nearest extent */
1951 struct ext4_ext_path *npath = NULL;
1952 int depth, len, err;
1953 ext4_lblk_t next;
1954 int mb_flags = 0, unwritten;
1955
1956 if (gb_flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_DELALLOC_RESERVE)
1957 mb_flags |= EXT4_MB_DELALLOC_RESERVED;
1958 if (unlikely(ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext) == 0)) {
1959 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext) == 0");
1960 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1961 }
1962 depth = ext_depth(inode);
1963 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
1964 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
1965 if (unlikely(path[depth].p_hdr == NULL)) {
1966 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "path[%d].p_hdr == NULL", depth);
1967 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
1968 }
1969
1970 /* try to insert block into found extent and return */
1971 if (ex && !(gb_flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_PRE_IO)) {
1972
1973 /*
1974 * Try to see whether we should rather test the extent on
1975 * right from ex, or from the left of ex. This is because
1976 * ext4_find_extent() can return either extent on the
1977 * left, or on the right from the searched position. This
1978 * will make merging more effective.
1979 */
1980 if (ex < EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh) &&
1981 (le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) +
1982 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex) <
1983 le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block))) {
1984 ex += 1;
1985 goto prepend;
1986 } else if ((ex > EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh)) &&
1987 (le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block) +
1988 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext) <
1989 le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)))
1990 ex -= 1;
1991
1992 /* Try to append newex to the ex */
1993 if (ext4_can_extents_be_merged(inode, ex, newext)) {
1994 ext_debug("append [%d]%d block to %u:[%d]%d"
1995 "(from %llu)\n",
1996 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(newext),
1997 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext),
1998 le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block),
1999 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex),
2000 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex),
2001 ext4_ext_pblock(ex));
2002 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode,
2003 path + depth);
2004 if (err)
2005 return err;
2006 unwritten = ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex);
2007 ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex)
2008 + ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext));
2009 if (unwritten)
2010 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex);
2011 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
2012 nearex = ex;
2013 goto merge;
2014 }
2015
2016prepend:
2017 /* Try to prepend newex to the ex */
2018 if (ext4_can_extents_be_merged(inode, newext, ex)) {
2019 ext_debug("prepend %u[%d]%d block to %u:[%d]%d"
2020 "(from %llu)\n",
2021 le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block),
2022 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(newext),
2023 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext),
2024 le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block),
2025 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex),
2026 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex),
2027 ext4_ext_pblock(ex));
2028 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode,
2029 path + depth);
2030 if (err)
2031 return err;
2032
2033 unwritten = ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex);
2034 ex->ee_block = newext->ee_block;
2035 ext4_ext_store_pblock(ex, ext4_ext_pblock(newext));
2036 ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex)
2037 + ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext));
2038 if (unwritten)
2039 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex);
2040 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
2041 nearex = ex;
2042 goto merge;
2043 }
2044 }
2045
2046 depth = ext_depth(inode);
2047 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
2048 if (le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries) < le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_max))
2049 goto has_space;
2050
2051 /* probably next leaf has space for us? */
2052 fex = EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh);
2053 next = EXT_MAX_BLOCKS;
2054 if (le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block) > le32_to_cpu(fex->ee_block))
2055 next = ext4_ext_next_leaf_block(path);
2056 if (next != EXT_MAX_BLOCKS) {
2057 ext_debug("next leaf block - %u\n", next);
2058 BUG_ON(npath != NULL);
2059 npath = ext4_find_extent(inode, next, NULL, 0);
2060 if (IS_ERR(npath))
2061 return PTR_ERR(npath);
2062 BUG_ON(npath->p_depth != path->p_depth);
2063 eh = npath[depth].p_hdr;
2064 if (le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries) < le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_max)) {
2065 ext_debug("next leaf isn't full(%d)\n",
2066 le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries));
2067 path = npath;
2068 goto has_space;
2069 }
2070 ext_debug("next leaf has no free space(%d,%d)\n",
2071 le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_entries), le16_to_cpu(eh->eh_max));
2072 }
2073
2074 /*
2075 * There is no free space in the found leaf.
2076 * We're gonna add a new leaf in the tree.
2077 */
2078 if (gb_flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_METADATA_NOFAIL)
2079 mb_flags |= EXT4_MB_USE_RESERVED;
2080 err = ext4_ext_create_new_leaf(handle, inode, mb_flags, gb_flags,
2081 ppath, newext);
2082 if (err)
2083 goto cleanup;
2084 depth = ext_depth(inode);
2085 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
2086
2087has_space:
2088 nearex = path[depth].p_ext;
2089
2090 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + depth);
2091 if (err)
2092 goto cleanup;
2093
2094 if (!nearex) {
2095 /* there is no extent in this leaf, create first one */
2096 ext_debug("first extent in the leaf: %u:%llu:[%d]%d\n",
2097 le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block),
2098 ext4_ext_pblock(newext),
2099 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(newext),
2100 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext));
2101 nearex = EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh);
2102 } else {
2103 if (le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block)
2104 > le32_to_cpu(nearex->ee_block)) {
2105 /* Insert after */
2106 ext_debug("insert %u:%llu:[%d]%d before: "
2107 "nearest %p\n",
2108 le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block),
2109 ext4_ext_pblock(newext),
2110 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(newext),
2111 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext),
2112 nearex);
2113 nearex++;
2114 } else {
2115 /* Insert before */
2116 BUG_ON(newext->ee_block == nearex->ee_block);
2117 ext_debug("insert %u:%llu:[%d]%d after: "
2118 "nearest %p\n",
2119 le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block),
2120 ext4_ext_pblock(newext),
2121 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(newext),
2122 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext),
2123 nearex);
2124 }
2125 len = EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh) - nearex + 1;
2126 if (len > 0) {
2127 ext_debug("insert %u:%llu:[%d]%d: "
2128 "move %d extents from 0x%p to 0x%p\n",
2129 le32_to_cpu(newext->ee_block),
2130 ext4_ext_pblock(newext),
2131 ext4_ext_is_unwritten(newext),
2132 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(newext),
2133 len, nearex, nearex + 1);
2134 memmove(nearex + 1, nearex,
2135 len * sizeof(struct ext4_extent));
2136 }
2137 }
2138
2139 le16_add_cpu(&eh->eh_entries, 1);
2140 path[depth].p_ext = nearex;
2141 nearex->ee_block = newext->ee_block;
2142 ext4_ext_store_pblock(nearex, ext4_ext_pblock(newext));
2143 nearex->ee_len = newext->ee_len;
2144
2145merge:
2146 /* try to merge extents */
2147 if (!(gb_flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_PRE_IO))
2148 ext4_ext_try_to_merge(handle, inode, path, nearex);
2149
2150
2151 /* time to correct all indexes above */
2152 err = ext4_ext_correct_indexes(handle, inode, path);
2153 if (err)
2154 goto cleanup;
2155
2156 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + path->p_depth);
2157
2158cleanup:
2159 ext4_ext_drop_refs(npath);
2160 kfree(npath);
2161 return err;
2162}
2163
2164static int ext4_fill_fiemap_extents(struct inode *inode,
2165 ext4_lblk_t block, ext4_lblk_t num,
2166 struct fiemap_extent_info *fieinfo)
2167{
2168 struct ext4_ext_path *path = NULL;
2169 struct ext4_extent *ex;
2170 struct extent_status es;
2171 ext4_lblk_t next, next_del, start = 0, end = 0;
2172 ext4_lblk_t last = block + num;
2173 int exists, depth = 0, err = 0;
2174 unsigned int flags = 0;
2175 unsigned char blksize_bits = inode->i_sb->s_blocksize_bits;
2176
2177 while (block < last && block != EXT_MAX_BLOCKS) {
2178 num = last - block;
2179 /* find extent for this block */
2180 down_read(&EXT4_I(inode)->i_data_sem);
2181
2182 path = ext4_find_extent(inode, block, &path, 0);
2183 if (IS_ERR(path)) {
2184 up_read(&EXT4_I(inode)->i_data_sem);
2185 err = PTR_ERR(path);
2186 path = NULL;
2187 break;
2188 }
2189
2190 depth = ext_depth(inode);
2191 if (unlikely(path[depth].p_hdr == NULL)) {
2192 up_read(&EXT4_I(inode)->i_data_sem);
2193 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "path[%d].p_hdr == NULL", depth);
2194 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
2195 break;
2196 }
2197 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
2198 next = ext4_ext_next_allocated_block(path);
2199
2200 flags = 0;
2201 exists = 0;
2202 if (!ex) {
2203 /* there is no extent yet, so try to allocate
2204 * all requested space */
2205 start = block;
2206 end = block + num;
2207 } else if (le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) > block) {
2208 /* need to allocate space before found extent */
2209 start = block;
2210 end = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
2211 if (block + num < end)
2212 end = block + num;
2213 } else if (block >= le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)
2214 + ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex)) {
2215 /* need to allocate space after found extent */
2216 start = block;
2217 end = block + num;
2218 if (end >= next)
2219 end = next;
2220 } else if (block >= le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)) {
2221 /*
2222 * some part of requested space is covered
2223 * by found extent
2224 */
2225 start = block;
2226 end = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)
2227 + ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
2228 if (block + num < end)
2229 end = block + num;
2230 exists = 1;
2231 } else {
2232 BUG();
2233 }
2234 BUG_ON(end <= start);
2235
2236 if (!exists) {
2237 es.es_lblk = start;
2238 es.es_len = end - start;
2239 es.es_pblk = 0;
2240 } else {
2241 es.es_lblk = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
2242 es.es_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
2243 es.es_pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex);
2244 if (ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex))
2245 flags |= FIEMAP_EXTENT_UNWRITTEN;
2246 }
2247
2248 /*
2249 * Find delayed extent and update es accordingly. We call
2250 * it even in !exists case to find out whether es is the
2251 * last existing extent or not.
2252 */
2253 next_del = ext4_find_delayed_extent(inode, &es);
2254 if (!exists && next_del) {
2255 exists = 1;
2256 flags |= (FIEMAP_EXTENT_DELALLOC |
2257 FIEMAP_EXTENT_UNKNOWN);
2258 }
2259 up_read(&EXT4_I(inode)->i_data_sem);
2260
2261 if (unlikely(es.es_len == 0)) {
2262 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "es.es_len == 0");
2263 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
2264 break;
2265 }
2266
2267 /*
2268 * This is possible iff next == next_del == EXT_MAX_BLOCKS.
2269 * we need to check next == EXT_MAX_BLOCKS because it is
2270 * possible that an extent is with unwritten and delayed
2271 * status due to when an extent is delayed allocated and
2272 * is allocated by fallocate status tree will track both of
2273 * them in a extent.
2274 *
2275 * So we could return a unwritten and delayed extent, and
2276 * its block is equal to 'next'.
2277 */
2278 if (next == next_del && next == EXT_MAX_BLOCKS) {
2279 flags |= FIEMAP_EXTENT_LAST;
2280 if (unlikely(next_del != EXT_MAX_BLOCKS ||
2281 next != EXT_MAX_BLOCKS)) {
2282 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
2283 "next extent == %u, next "
2284 "delalloc extent = %u",
2285 next, next_del);
2286 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
2287 break;
2288 }
2289 }
2290
2291 if (exists) {
2292 err = fiemap_fill_next_extent(fieinfo,
2293 (__u64)es.es_lblk << blksize_bits,
2294 (__u64)es.es_pblk << blksize_bits,
2295 (__u64)es.es_len << blksize_bits,
2296 flags);
2297 if (err < 0)
2298 break;
2299 if (err == 1) {
2300 err = 0;
2301 break;
2302 }
2303 }
2304
2305 block = es.es_lblk + es.es_len;
2306 }
2307
2308 ext4_ext_drop_refs(path);
2309 kfree(path);
2310 return err;
2311}
2312
2313/*
2314 * ext4_ext_determine_hole - determine hole around given block
2315 * @inode: inode we lookup in
2316 * @path: path in extent tree to @lblk
2317 * @lblk: pointer to logical block around which we want to determine hole
2318 *
2319 * Determine hole length (and start if easily possible) around given logical
2320 * block. We don't try too hard to find the beginning of the hole but @path
2321 * actually points to extent before @lblk, we provide it.
2322 *
2323 * The function returns the length of a hole starting at @lblk. We update @lblk
2324 * to the beginning of the hole if we managed to find it.
2325 */
2326static ext4_lblk_t ext4_ext_determine_hole(struct inode *inode,
2327 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
2328 ext4_lblk_t *lblk)
2329{
2330 int depth = ext_depth(inode);
2331 struct ext4_extent *ex;
2332 ext4_lblk_t len;
2333
2334 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
2335 if (ex == NULL) {
2336 /* there is no extent yet, so gap is [0;-] */
2337 *lblk = 0;
2338 len = EXT_MAX_BLOCKS;
2339 } else if (*lblk < le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)) {
2340 len = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) - *lblk;
2341 } else if (*lblk >= le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)
2342 + ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex)) {
2343 ext4_lblk_t next;
2344
2345 *lblk = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) + ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
2346 next = ext4_ext_next_allocated_block(path);
2347 BUG_ON(next == *lblk);
2348 len = next - *lblk;
2349 } else {
2350 BUG();
2351 }
2352 return len;
2353}
2354
2355/*
2356 * ext4_ext_put_gap_in_cache:
2357 * calculate boundaries of the gap that the requested block fits into
2358 * and cache this gap
2359 */
2360static void
2361ext4_ext_put_gap_in_cache(struct inode *inode, ext4_lblk_t hole_start,
2362 ext4_lblk_t hole_len)
2363{
2364 struct extent_status es;
2365
2366 ext4_es_find_delayed_extent_range(inode, hole_start,
2367 hole_start + hole_len - 1, &es);
2368 if (es.es_len) {
2369 /* There's delayed extent containing lblock? */
2370 if (es.es_lblk <= hole_start)
2371 return;
2372 hole_len = min(es.es_lblk - hole_start, hole_len);
2373 }
2374 ext_debug(" -> %u:%u\n", hole_start, hole_len);
2375 ext4_es_insert_extent(inode, hole_start, hole_len, ~0,
2376 EXTENT_STATUS_HOLE);
2377}

2379/*
2380 * ext4_ext_rm_idx:
2381 * removes index from the index block.
2382 */
2383static int ext4_ext_rm_idx(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
2384 struct ext4_ext_path *path, int depth)
2385{
2386 int err;
2387 ext4_fsblk_t leaf;
2388
2389 /* free index block */
2390 depth--;
2391 path = path + depth;
2392 leaf = ext4_idx_pblock(path->p_idx);
2393 if (unlikely(path->p_hdr->eh_entries == 0)) {
2394 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "path->p_hdr->eh_entries == 0");
2395 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
2396 }
2397 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path);
2398 if (err)
2399 return err;
2400
2401 if (path->p_idx != EXT_LAST_INDEX(path->p_hdr)) {
2402 int len = EXT_LAST_INDEX(path->p_hdr) - path->p_idx;
2403 len *= sizeof(struct ext4_extent_idx);
2404 memmove(path->p_idx, path->p_idx + 1, len);
2405 }
2406
2407 le16_add_cpu(&path->p_hdr->eh_entries, -1);
2408 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path);
2409 if (err)
2410 return err;
2411 ext_debug("index is empty, remove it, free block %llu\n", leaf);
2412 trace_ext4_ext_rm_idx(inode, leaf);
2413
2414 ext4_free_blocks(handle, inode, NULL, leaf, 1,
2415 EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_METADATA | EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_FORGET);
2416
2417 while (--depth >= 0) {
2418 if (path->p_idx != EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path->p_hdr))
2419 break;
2420 path--;
2421 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path);
2422 if (err)
2423 break;
2424 path->p_idx->ei_block = (path+1)->p_idx->ei_block;
2425 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path);
2426 if (err)
2427 break;
2428 }
2429 return err;
2430}
