2432/*
2433 * ext4_ext_calc_credits_for_single_extent:
2434 * This routine returns max. credits that needed to insert an extent
2435 * to the extent tree.
2436 * When pass the actual path, the caller should calculate credits
2437 * under i_data_sem.
2438 */
2439int ext4_ext_calc_credits_for_single_extent(struct inode *inode, int nrblocks,
2440 struct ext4_ext_path *path)
2441{
2442 if (path) {
2443 int depth = ext_depth(inode);
2444 int ret = 0;
2445
2446 /* probably there is space in leaf? */
2447 if (le16_to_cpu(path[depth].p_hdr->eh_entries)
2448 < le16_to_cpu(path[depth].p_hdr->eh_max)) {
2449
2450 /*
2451 * There are some space in the leaf tree, no
2452 * need to account for leaf block credit
2453 *
2454 * bitmaps and block group descriptor blocks
2455 * and other metadata blocks still need to be
2456 * accounted.
2457 */
2458 /* 1 bitmap, 1 block group descriptor */
2459 ret = 2 + EXT4_META_TRANS_BLOCKS(inode->i_sb);
2460 return ret;
2461 }
2462 }
2463
2464 return ext4_chunk_trans_blocks(inode, nrblocks);
2465}
2466
2467/*
2468 * How many index/leaf blocks need to change/allocate to add @extents extents?
2469 *
2470 * If we add a single extent, then in the worse case, each tree level
2471 * index/leaf need to be changed in case of the tree split.
2472 *
2473 * If more extents are inserted, they could cause the whole tree split more
2474 * than once, but this is really rare.
2475 */
2476int ext4_ext_index_trans_blocks(struct inode *inode, int extents)
2477{
2478 int index;
2479 int depth;
2480
2481 /* If we are converting the inline data, only one is needed here. */
2482 if (ext4_has_inline_data(inode))
2483 return 1;
2484
2485 depth = ext_depth(inode);
2486
2487 if (extents <= 1)
2488 index = depth * 2;
2489 else
2490 index = depth * 3;
2491
2492 return index;
2493}
2494
2495static inline int get_default_free_blocks_flags(struct inode *inode)
2496{
2497 if (S_ISDIR(inode->i_mode) || S_ISLNK(inode->i_mode) ||
2498 ext4_test_inode_flag(inode, EXT4_INODE_EA_INODE))
2499 return EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_METADATA | EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_FORGET;
2500 else if (ext4_should_journal_data(inode))
2501 return EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_FORGET;
2502 return 0;
2503}
2504
2505static int ext4_remove_blocks(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
2506 struct ext4_extent *ex,
2507 long long *partial_cluster,
2508 ext4_lblk_t from, ext4_lblk_t to)
2509{
2510 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb);
2511 unsigned short ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
2512 ext4_fsblk_t pblk;
2513 int flags = get_default_free_blocks_flags(inode);
2514
2515 /*
2516 * For bigalloc file systems, we never free a partial cluster
2517 * at the beginning of the extent. Instead, we make a note
2518 * that we tried freeing the cluster, and check to see if we
2519 * need to free it on a subsequent call to ext4_remove_blocks,
2520 * or at the end of ext4_ext_rm_leaf or ext4_ext_remove_space.
2521 */
2522 flags |= EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_NOFREE_FIRST_CLUSTER;
2523
2524 trace_ext4_remove_blocks(inode, ex, from, to, *partial_cluster);
2525 /*
2526 * If we have a partial cluster, and it's different from the
2527 * cluster of the last block, we need to explicitly free the
2528 * partial cluster here.
2529 */
2530 pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex) + ee_len - 1;
2531 if (*partial_cluster > 0 &&
2532 *partial_cluster != (long long) EXT4_B2C(sbi, pblk)) {
2533 ext4_free_blocks(handle, inode, NULL,
2534 EXT4_C2B(sbi, *partial_cluster),
2535 sbi->s_cluster_ratio, flags);
2536 *partial_cluster = 0;
2537 }
2538
2539#ifdef EXTENTS_STATS
2540 {
2541 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb);
2542 spin_lock(&sbi->s_ext_stats_lock);
2543 sbi->s_ext_blocks += ee_len;
2544 sbi->s_ext_extents++;
2545 if (ee_len < sbi->s_ext_min)
2546 sbi->s_ext_min = ee_len;
2547 if (ee_len > sbi->s_ext_max)
2548 sbi->s_ext_max = ee_len;
2549 if (ext_depth(inode) > sbi->s_depth_max)
2550 sbi->s_depth_max = ext_depth(inode);
2551 spin_unlock(&sbi->s_ext_stats_lock);
2552 }
2553#endif
2554 if (from >= le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block)
2555 && to == le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) + ee_len - 1) {
2556 /* tail removal */
2557 ext4_lblk_t num;
2558 long long first_cluster;
2559
2560 num = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block) + ee_len - from;
2561 pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex) + ee_len - num;
2562 /*
2563 * Usually we want to free partial cluster at the end of the
2564 * extent, except for the situation when the cluster is still
2565 * used by any other extent (partial_cluster is negative).
2566 */
2567 if (*partial_cluster < 0 &&
2568 *partial_cluster == -(long long) EXT4_B2C(sbi, pblk+num-1))
2569 flags |= EXT4_FREE_BLOCKS_NOFREE_LAST_CLUSTER;
2570
2571 ext_debug("free last %u blocks starting %llu partial %lld\n",
2572 num, pblk, *partial_cluster);
2573 ext4_free_blocks(handle, inode, NULL, pblk, num, flags);
2574 /*
2575 * If the block range to be freed didn't start at the
2576 * beginning of a cluster, and we removed the entire
2577 * extent and the cluster is not used by any other extent,
2578 * save the partial cluster here, since we might need to
2579 * delete if we determine that the truncate or punch hole
2580 * operation has removed all of the blocks in the cluster.
2581 * If that cluster is used by another extent, preserve its
2582 * negative value so it isn't freed later on.
2583 *
2584 * If the whole extent wasn't freed, we've reached the
2585 * start of the truncated/punched region and have finished
2586 * removing blocks. If there's a partial cluster here it's
2587 * shared with the remainder of the extent and is no longer
2588 * a candidate for removal.
2589 */
2590 if (EXT4_PBLK_COFF(sbi, pblk) && ee_len == num) {
2591 first_cluster = (long long) EXT4_B2C(sbi, pblk);
2592 if (first_cluster != -*partial_cluster)
2593 *partial_cluster = first_cluster;
2594 } else {
2595 *partial_cluster = 0;
2596 }
2597 } else
2598 ext4_error(sbi->s_sb, "strange request: removal(2) "
2599 "%u-%u from %u:%u",
2600 from, to, le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block), ee_len);
2601 return 0;
2602}
2603
2604
2605/*
2606 * ext4_ext_rm_leaf() Removes the extents associated with the
2607 * blocks appearing between "start" and "end". Both "start"
2608 * and "end" must appear in the same extent or EIO is returned.
2609 *
2610 * @handle: The journal handle
2611 * @inode: The files inode
2612 * @path: The path to the leaf
2613 * @partial_cluster: The cluster which we'll have to free if all extents
2614 * has been released from it. However, if this value is
2615 * negative, it's a cluster just to the right of the
2616 * punched region and it must not be freed.
2617 * @start: The first block to remove
2618 * @end: The last block to remove
2619 */
2620static int
2621ext4_ext_rm_leaf(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
2622 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
2623 long long *partial_cluster,
2624 ext4_lblk_t start, ext4_lblk_t end)
2625{
2626 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb);
2627 int err = 0, correct_index = 0;
2628 int depth = ext_depth(inode), credits;
2629 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
2630 ext4_lblk_t a, b;
2631 unsigned num;
2632 ext4_lblk_t ex_ee_block;
2633 unsigned short ex_ee_len;
2634 unsigned unwritten = 0;
2635 struct ext4_extent *ex;
2636 ext4_fsblk_t pblk;
2637
2638 /* the header must be checked already in ext4_ext_remove_space() */
2639 ext_debug("truncate since %u in leaf to %u\n", start, end);
2640 if (!path[depth].p_hdr)
2641 path[depth].p_hdr = ext_block_hdr(path[depth].p_bh);
2642 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
2643 if (unlikely(path[depth].p_hdr == NULL)) {
2644 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "path[%d].p_hdr == NULL", depth);
2645 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
2646 }
2647 /* find where to start removing */
2648 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
2649 if (!ex)
2650 ex = EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh);
2651
2652 ex_ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
2653 ex_ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
2654
2655 trace_ext4_ext_rm_leaf(inode, start, ex, *partial_cluster);
2656
2657 while (ex >= EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh) &&
2658 ex_ee_block + ex_ee_len > start) {
2659
2660 if (ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex))
2661 unwritten = 1;
2662 else
2663 unwritten = 0;
2664
2665 ext_debug("remove ext %u:[%d]%d\n", ex_ee_block,
2666 unwritten, ex_ee_len);
2667 path[depth].p_ext = ex;
2668
2669 a = ex_ee_block > start ? ex_ee_block : start;
2670 b = ex_ee_block+ex_ee_len - 1 < end ?
2671 ex_ee_block+ex_ee_len - 1 : end;
2672
2673 ext_debug(" border %u:%u\n", a, b);
2674
2675 /* If this extent is beyond the end of the hole, skip it */
2676 if (end < ex_ee_block) {
2677 /*
2678 * We're going to skip this extent and move to another,
2679 * so note that its first cluster is in use to avoid
2680 * freeing it when removing blocks. Eventually, the
2681 * right edge of the truncated/punched region will
2682 * be just to the left.
2683 */
2684 if (sbi->s_cluster_ratio > 1) {
2685 pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex);
2686 *partial_cluster =
2687 -(long long) EXT4_B2C(sbi, pblk);
2688 }
2689 ex--;
2690 ex_ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
2691 ex_ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
2692 continue;
2693 } else if (b != ex_ee_block + ex_ee_len - 1) {
2694 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
2695 "can not handle truncate %u:%u "
2696 "on extent %u:%u",
2697 start, end, ex_ee_block,
2698 ex_ee_block + ex_ee_len - 1);
2699 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
2700 goto out;
2701 } else if (a != ex_ee_block) {
2702 /* remove tail of the extent */
2703 num = a - ex_ee_block;
2704 } else {
2705 /* remove whole extent: excellent! */
2706 num = 0;
2707 }
2708 /*
2709 * 3 for leaf, sb, and inode plus 2 (bmap and group
2710 * descriptor) for each block group; assume two block
2711 * groups plus ex_ee_len/blocks_per_block_group for
2712 * the worst case
2713 */
2714 credits = 7 + 2*(ex_ee_len/EXT4_BLOCKS_PER_GROUP(inode->i_sb));
2715 if (ex == EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh)) {
2716 correct_index = 1;
2717 credits += (ext_depth(inode)) + 1;
2718 }
2719 credits += EXT4_MAXQUOTAS_TRANS_BLOCKS(inode->i_sb);
2720
2721 err = ext4_ext_truncate_extend_restart(handle, inode, credits);
2722 if (err)
2723 goto out;
2724
2725 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + depth);
2726 if (err)
2727 goto out;
2728
2729 err = ext4_remove_blocks(handle, inode, ex, partial_cluster,
2730 a, b);
2731 if (err)
2732 goto out;
2733
2734 if (num == 0)
2735 /* this extent is removed; mark slot entirely unused */
2736 ext4_ext_store_pblock(ex, 0);
2737
2738 ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(num);
2739 /*
2740 * Do not mark unwritten if all the blocks in the
2741 * extent have been removed.
2742 */
2743 if (unwritten && num)
2744 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex);
2745 /*
2746 * If the extent was completely released,
2747 * we need to remove it from the leaf
2748 */
2749 if (num == 0) {
2750 if (end != EXT_MAX_BLOCKS - 1) {
2751 /*
2752 * For hole punching, we need to scoot all the
2753 * extents up when an extent is removed so that
2754 * we dont have blank extents in the middle
2755 */
2756 memmove(ex, ex+1, (EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh) - ex) *
2757 sizeof(struct ext4_extent));
2758
2759 /* Now get rid of the one at the end */
2760 memset(EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh), 0,
2761 sizeof(struct ext4_extent));
2762 }
2763 le16_add_cpu(&eh->eh_entries, -1);
2764 }
2765
2766 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + depth);
2767 if (err)
2768 goto out;
2769
2770 ext_debug("new extent: %u:%u:%llu\n", ex_ee_block, num,
2771 ext4_ext_pblock(ex));
2772 ex--;
2773 ex_ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
2774 ex_ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
2775 }
2776
2777 if (correct_index && eh->eh_entries)
2778 err = ext4_ext_correct_indexes(handle, inode, path);
2779
2780 /*
2781 * If there's a partial cluster and at least one extent remains in
2782 * the leaf, free the partial cluster if it isn't shared with the
2783 * current extent. If it is shared with the current extent
2784 * we zero partial_cluster because we've reached the start of the
2785 * truncated/punched region and we're done removing blocks.
2786 */
2787 if (*partial_cluster > 0 && ex >= EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh)) {
2788 pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex) + ex_ee_len - 1;
2789 if (*partial_cluster != (long long) EXT4_B2C(sbi, pblk)) {
2790 ext4_free_blocks(handle, inode, NULL,
2791 EXT4_C2B(sbi, *partial_cluster),
2792 sbi->s_cluster_ratio,
2793 get_default_free_blocks_flags(inode));
2794 }
2795 *partial_cluster = 0;
2796 }
2797
2798 /* if this leaf is free, then we should
2799 * remove it from index block above */
2800 if (err == 0 && eh->eh_entries == 0 && path[depth].p_bh != NULL)
2801 err = ext4_ext_rm_idx(handle, inode, path, depth);
2802
2803out:
2804 return err;
2805}
2806
2807/*
2808 * ext4_ext_more_to_rm:
2809 * returns 1 if current index has to be freed (even partial)
2810 */
2811static int
2812ext4_ext_more_to_rm(struct ext4_ext_path *path)
2813{
2814 BUG_ON(path->p_idx == NULL);
2815
2816 if (path->p_idx < EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path->p_hdr))
2817 return 0;
2818
2819 /*
2820 * if truncate on deeper level happened, it wasn't partial,
2821 * so we have to consider current index for truncation
2822 */
2823 if (le16_to_cpu(path->p_hdr->eh_entries) == path->p_block)
2824 return 0;
2825 return 1;
2826}
2827
2828int ext4_ext_remove_space(struct inode *inode, ext4_lblk_t start,
2829 ext4_lblk_t end)
2830{
2831 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb);
2832 int depth = ext_depth(inode);
2833 struct ext4_ext_path *path = NULL;
2834 long long partial_cluster = 0;
2835 handle_t *handle;
2836 int i = 0, err = 0;
2837
2838 ext_debug("truncate since %u to %u\n", start, end);
2839
2840 /* probably first extent we're gonna free will be last in block */
2841 handle = ext4_journal_start(inode, EXT4_HT_TRUNCATE, depth + 1);
2842 if (IS_ERR(handle))
2843 return PTR_ERR(handle);
2844
2845again:
2846 trace_ext4_ext_remove_space(inode, start, end, depth);
2847
2848 /*
2849 * Check if we are removing extents inside the extent tree. If that
2850 * is the case, we are going to punch a hole inside the extent tree
2851 * so we have to check whether we need to split the extent covering
2852 * the last block to remove so we can easily remove the part of it
2853 * in ext4_ext_rm_leaf().
2854 */
2855 if (end < EXT_MAX_BLOCKS - 1) {
2856 struct ext4_extent *ex;
2857 ext4_lblk_t ee_block, ex_end, lblk;
2858 ext4_fsblk_t pblk;
2859
2860 /* find extent for or closest extent to this block */
2861 path = ext4_find_extent(inode, end, NULL, EXT4_EX_NOCACHE);
2862 if (IS_ERR(path)) {
2863 ext4_journal_stop(handle);
2864 return PTR_ERR(path);
2865 }
2866 depth = ext_depth(inode);
2867 /* Leaf not may not exist only if inode has no blocks at all */
2868 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
2869 if (!ex) {
2870 if (depth) {
2871 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode,
2872 "path[%d].p_hdr == NULL",
2873 depth);
2874 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
2875 }
2876 goto out;
2877 }
2878
2879 ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
2880 ex_end = ee_block + ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex) - 1;
2881
2882 /*
2883 * See if the last block is inside the extent, if so split
2884 * the extent at 'end' block so we can easily remove the
2885 * tail of the first part of the split extent in
2886 * ext4_ext_rm_leaf().
2887 */
2888 if (end >= ee_block && end < ex_end) {
2889
2890 /*
2891 * If we're going to split the extent, note that
2892 * the cluster containing the block after 'end' is
2893 * in use to avoid freeing it when removing blocks.
2894 */
2895 if (sbi->s_cluster_ratio > 1) {
2896 pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex) + end - ee_block + 2;
2897 partial_cluster =
2898 -(long long) EXT4_B2C(sbi, pblk);
2899 }
2900
2901 /*
2902 * Split the extent in two so that 'end' is the last
2903 * block in the first new extent. Also we should not
2904 * fail removing space due to ENOSPC so try to use
2905 * reserved block if that happens.
2906 */
2907 err = ext4_force_split_extent_at(handle, inode, &path,
2908 end + 1, 1);
2909 if (err < 0)
2910 goto out;
2911
2912 } else if (sbi->s_cluster_ratio > 1 && end >= ex_end) {
2913 /*
2914 * If there's an extent to the right its first cluster
2915 * contains the immediate right boundary of the
2916 * truncated/punched region. Set partial_cluster to
2917 * its negative value so it won't be freed if shared
2918 * with the current extent. The end < ee_block case
2919 * is handled in ext4_ext_rm_leaf().
2920 */
2921 lblk = ex_end + 1;
2922 err = ext4_ext_search_right(inode, path, &lblk, &pblk,
2923 &ex);
2924 if (err)
2925 goto out;
2926 if (pblk)
2927 partial_cluster =
2928 -(long long) EXT4_B2C(sbi, pblk);
2929 }
2930 }
2931 /*
2932 * We start scanning from right side, freeing all the blocks
2933 * after i_size and walking into the tree depth-wise.
2934 */
2935 depth = ext_depth(inode);
2936 if (path) {
2937 int k = i = depth;
2938 while (--k > 0)
2939 path[k].p_block =
2940 le16_to_cpu(path[k].p_hdr->eh_entries)+1;
2941 } else {
2942 path = kzalloc(sizeof(struct ext4_ext_path) * (depth + 1),
2943 GFP_NOFS);
2944 if (path == NULL) {
2945 ext4_journal_stop(handle);
2946 return -ENOMEM;
2947 }
2948 path[0].p_maxdepth = path[0].p_depth = depth;
2949 path[0].p_hdr = ext_inode_hdr(inode);
2950 i = 0;
2951
2952 if (ext4_ext_check(inode, path[0].p_hdr, depth, 0)) {
2953 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
2954 goto out;
2955 }
2956 }
2957 err = 0;
2958
2959 while (i >= 0 && err == 0) {
2960 if (i == depth) {
2961 /* this is leaf block */
2962 err = ext4_ext_rm_leaf(handle, inode, path,
2963 &partial_cluster, start,
2964 end);
2965 /* root level has p_bh == NULL, brelse() eats this */
2966 brelse(path[i].p_bh);
2967 path[i].p_bh = NULL;
2968 i--;
2969 continue;
2970 }
2971
2972 /* this is index block */
2973 if (!path[i].p_hdr) {
2974 ext_debug("initialize header\n");
2975 path[i].p_hdr = ext_block_hdr(path[i].p_bh);
2976 }
2977
2978 if (!path[i].p_idx) {
2979 /* this level hasn't been touched yet */
2980 path[i].p_idx = EXT_LAST_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr);
2981 path[i].p_block = le16_to_cpu(path[i].p_hdr->eh_entries)+1;
2982 ext_debug("init index ptr: hdr 0x%p, num %d\n",
2983 path[i].p_hdr,
2984 le16_to_cpu(path[i].p_hdr->eh_entries));
2985 } else {
2986 /* we were already here, see at next index */
2987 path[i].p_idx--;
2988 }
2989
2990 ext_debug("level %d - index, first 0x%p, cur 0x%p\n",
2991 i, EXT_FIRST_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr),
2992 path[i].p_idx);
2993 if (ext4_ext_more_to_rm(path + i)) {
2994 struct buffer_head *bh;
2995 /* go to the next level */
2996 ext_debug("move to level %d (block %llu)\n",
2997 i + 1, ext4_idx_pblock(path[i].p_idx));
2998 memset(path + i + 1, 0, sizeof(*path));
2999 bh = read_extent_tree_block(inode,
3000 ext4_idx_pblock(path[i].p_idx), depth - i - 1,
3001 EXT4_EX_NOCACHE);
3002 if (IS_ERR(bh)) {
3003 /* should we reset i_size? */
3004 err = PTR_ERR(bh);
3005 break;
3006 }
3007 /* Yield here to deal with large extent trees.
3008 * Should be a no-op if we did IO above. */
3009 cond_resched();
3010 if (WARN_ON(i + 1 > depth)) {
3011 err = -EFSCORRUPTED;
3012 break;
3013 }
3014 path[i + 1].p_bh = bh;
3015
3016 /* save actual number of indexes since this
3017 * number is changed at the next iteration */
3018 path[i].p_block = le16_to_cpu(path[i].p_hdr->eh_entries);
3019 i++;
3020 } else {
3021 /* we finished processing this index, go up */
3022 if (path[i].p_hdr->eh_entries == 0 && i > 0) {
3023 /* index is empty, remove it;
3024 * handle must be already prepared by the
3025 * truncatei_leaf() */
3026 err = ext4_ext_rm_idx(handle, inode, path, i);
3027 }
3028 /* root level has p_bh == NULL, brelse() eats this */
3029 brelse(path[i].p_bh);
3030 path[i].p_bh = NULL;
3031 i--;
3032 ext_debug("return to level %d\n", i);
3033 }
3034 }
3035
3036 trace_ext4_ext_remove_space_done(inode, start, end, depth,
3037 partial_cluster, path->p_hdr->eh_entries);
3038
3039 /*
3040 * If we still have something in the partial cluster and we have removed
3041 * even the first extent, then we should free the blocks in the partial
3042 * cluster as well. (This code will only run when there are no leaves
3043 * to the immediate left of the truncated/punched region.)
3044 */
3045 if (partial_cluster > 0 && err == 0) {
3046 /* don't zero partial_cluster since it's not used afterwards */
3047 ext4_free_blocks(handle, inode, NULL,
3048 EXT4_C2B(sbi, partial_cluster),
3049 sbi->s_cluster_ratio,
3050 get_default_free_blocks_flags(inode));
3051 }
3052
3053 /* TODO: flexible tree reduction should be here */
3054 if (path->p_hdr->eh_entries == 0) {
3055 /*
3056 * truncate to zero freed all the tree,
3057 * so we need to correct eh_depth
3058 */
3059 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path);
3060 if (err == 0) {
3061 ext_inode_hdr(inode)->eh_depth = 0;
3062 ext_inode_hdr(inode)->eh_max =
3063 cpu_to_le16(ext4_ext_space_root(inode, 0));
3064 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path);
3065 }
3066 }
3067out:
3068 ext4_ext_drop_refs(path);
3069 kfree(path);
3070 path = NULL;
3071 if (err == -EAGAIN)
3072 goto again;
3073 ext4_journal_stop(handle);
3074
3075 return err;
3076}

3158/*
3159 * ext4_split_extent_at() splits an extent at given block.
3160 *
3161 * @handle: the journal handle
3162 * @inode: the file inode
3163 * @path: the path to the extent
3164 * @split: the logical block where the extent is splitted.
3165 * @split_flags: indicates if the extent could be zeroout if split fails, and
3166 * the states(init or unwritten) of new extents.
3167 * @flags: flags used to insert new extent to extent tree.
3168 *
3169 *
3170 * Splits extent [a, b] into two extents [a, @split) and [@split, b], states
3171 * of which are deterimined by split_flag.
3172 *
3173 * There are two cases:
3174 * a> the extent are splitted into two extent.
3175 * b> split is not needed, and just mark the extent.
3176 *
3177 * return 0 on success.
3178 */
3179static int ext4_split_extent_at(handle_t *handle,
3180 struct inode *inode,
3181 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath,
3182 ext4_lblk_t split,
3183 int split_flag,
3184 int flags)
3185{
3186 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
3187 ext4_fsblk_t newblock;
3188 ext4_lblk_t ee_block;
3189 struct ext4_extent *ex, newex, orig_ex, zero_ex;
3190 struct ext4_extent *ex2 = NULL;
3191 unsigned int ee_len, depth;
3192 int err = 0;
3193
3194 BUG_ON((split_flag & (EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID1 | EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID2)) ==
3195 (EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID1 | EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID2));
3196
3197 ext_debug("ext4_split_extents_at: inode %lu, logical"
3198 "block %llu\n", inode->i_ino, (unsigned long long)split);
3199
3200 ext4_ext_show_leaf(inode, path);
3201
3202 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3203 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3204 ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
3205 ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
3206 newblock = split - ee_block + ext4_ext_pblock(ex);
3207
3208 BUG_ON(split < ee_block || split >= (ee_block + ee_len));
3209 BUG_ON(!ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex) &&
3210 split_flag & (EXT4_EXT_MAY_ZEROOUT |
3211 EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT1 |
3212 EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT2));
3213
3214 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + depth);
3215 if (err)
3216 goto out;
3217
3218 if (split == ee_block) {
3219 /*
3220 * case b: block @split is the block that the extent begins with
3221 * then we just change the state of the extent, and splitting
3222 * is not needed.
3223 */
3224 if (split_flag & EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT2)
3225 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex);
3226 else
3227 ext4_ext_mark_initialized(ex);
3228
3229 if (!(flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_PRE_IO))
3230 ext4_ext_try_to_merge(handle, inode, path, ex);
3231
3232 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + path->p_depth);
3233 goto out;
3234 }
3235
3236 /* case a */
3237 memcpy(&orig_ex, ex, sizeof(orig_ex));
3238 ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(split - ee_block);
3239 if (split_flag & EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT1)
3240 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex);
3241
3242 /*
3243 * path may lead to new leaf, not to original leaf any more
3244 * after ext4_ext_insert_extent() returns,
3245 */
3246 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + depth);
3247 if (err)
3248 goto fix_extent_len;
3249
3250 ex2 = &newex;
3251 ex2->ee_block = cpu_to_le32(split);
3252 ex2->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(ee_len - (split - ee_block));
3253 ext4_ext_store_pblock(ex2, newblock);
3254 if (split_flag & EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT2)
3255 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex2);
3256
3257 err = ext4_ext_insert_extent(handle, inode, ppath, &newex, flags);
3258 if (err == -ENOSPC && (EXT4_EXT_MAY_ZEROOUT & split_flag)) {
3259 if (split_flag & (EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID1|EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID2)) {
3260 if (split_flag & EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID1) {
3261 err = ext4_ext_zeroout(inode, ex2);
3262 zero_ex.ee_block = ex2->ee_block;
3263 zero_ex.ee_len = cpu_to_le16(
3264 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex2));
3265 ext4_ext_store_pblock(&zero_ex,
3266 ext4_ext_pblock(ex2));
3267 } else {
3268 err = ext4_ext_zeroout(inode, ex);
3269 zero_ex.ee_block = ex->ee_block;
3270 zero_ex.ee_len = cpu_to_le16(
3271 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex));
3272 ext4_ext_store_pblock(&zero_ex,
3273 ext4_ext_pblock(ex));
3274 }
3275 } else {
3276 err = ext4_ext_zeroout(inode, &orig_ex);
3277 zero_ex.ee_block = orig_ex.ee_block;
3278 zero_ex.ee_len = cpu_to_le16(
3279 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(&orig_ex));
3280 ext4_ext_store_pblock(&zero_ex,
3281 ext4_ext_pblock(&orig_ex));
3282 }
3283
3284 if (err)
3285 goto fix_extent_len;
3286 /* update the extent length and mark as initialized */
3287 ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(ee_len);
3288 ext4_ext_try_to_merge(handle, inode, path, ex);
3289 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + path->p_depth);
3290 if (err)
3291 goto fix_extent_len;
3292
3293 /* update extent status tree */
3294 err = ext4_zeroout_es(inode, &zero_ex);
3295
3296 goto out;
3297 } else if (err)
3298 goto fix_extent_len;
3299
3300out:
3301 ext4_ext_show_leaf(inode, path);
3302 return err;
3303
3304fix_extent_len:
3305 ex->ee_len = orig_ex.ee_len;
3306 ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + path->p_depth);
3307 return err;
3308}

3310/*
3311 * ext4_split_extents() splits an extent and mark extent which is covered
3312 * by @map as split_flags indicates
3313 *
3314 * It may result in splitting the extent into multiple extents (up to three)
3315 * There are three possibilities:
3316 * a> There is no split required
3317 * b> Splits in two extents: Split is happening at either end of the extent
3318 * c> Splits in three extents: Somone is splitting in middle of the extent
3319 *
3320 */
3321static int ext4_split_extent(handle_t *handle,
3322 struct inode *inode,
3323 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath,
3324 struct ext4_map_blocks *map,
3325 int split_flag,
3326 int flags)
3327{
3328 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
3329 ext4_lblk_t ee_block;
3330 struct ext4_extent *ex;
3331 unsigned int ee_len, depth;
3332 int err = 0;
3333 int unwritten;
3334 int split_flag1, flags1;
3335 int allocated = map->m_len;
3336
3337 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3338 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3339 ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
3340 ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
3341 unwritten = ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex);
3342
3343 if (map->m_lblk + map->m_len < ee_block + ee_len) {
3344 split_flag1 = split_flag & EXT4_EXT_MAY_ZEROOUT;
3345 flags1 = flags | EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_PRE_IO;
3346 if (unwritten)
3347 split_flag1 |= EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT1 |
3348 EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT2;
3349 if (split_flag & EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID2)
3350 split_flag1 |= EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID1;
3351 err = ext4_split_extent_at(handle, inode, ppath,
3352 map->m_lblk + map->m_len, split_flag1, flags1);
3353 if (err)
3354 goto out;
3355 } else {
3356 allocated = ee_len - (map->m_lblk - ee_block);
3357 }
3358 /*
3359 * Update path is required because previous ext4_split_extent_at() may
3360 * result in split of original leaf or extent zeroout.
3361 */
3362 path = ext4_find_extent(inode, map->m_lblk, ppath, 0);
3363 if (IS_ERR(path))
3364 return PTR_ERR(path);
3365 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3366 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3367 if (!ex) {
3368 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "unexpected hole at %lu",
3369 (unsigned long) map->m_lblk);
3370 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
3371 }
3372 unwritten = ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex);
3373 split_flag1 = 0;
3374
3375 if (map->m_lblk >= ee_block) {
3376 split_flag1 = split_flag & EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID2;
3377 if (unwritten) {
3378 split_flag1 |= EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT1;
3379 split_flag1 |= split_flag & (EXT4_EXT_MAY_ZEROOUT |
3380 EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT2);
3381 }
3382 err = ext4_split_extent_at(handle, inode, ppath,
3383 map->m_lblk, split_flag1, flags);
3384 if (err)
3385 goto out;
3386 }
3387
3388 ext4_ext_show_leaf(inode, path);
3389out:
3390 return err ? err : allocated;
3391}

3393/*
3394 * This function is called by ext4_ext_map_blocks() if someone tries to write
3395 * to an unwritten extent. It may result in splitting the unwritten
3396 * extent into multiple extents (up to three - one initialized and two
3397 * unwritten).
3398 * There are three possibilities:
3399 * a> There is no split required: Entire extent should be initialized
3400 * b> Splits in two extents: Write is happening at either end of the extent
3401 * c> Splits in three extents: Somone is writing in middle of the extent
3402 *
3403 * Pre-conditions:
3404 * - The extent pointed to by 'path' is unwritten.
3405 * - The extent pointed to by 'path' contains a superset
3406 * of the logical span [map->m_lblk, map->m_lblk + map->m_len).
3407 *
3408 * Post-conditions on success:
3409 * - the returned value is the number of blocks beyond map->l_lblk
3410 * that are allocated and initialized.
3411 * It is guaranteed to be >= map->m_len.
3412 */
3413static int ext4_ext_convert_to_initialized(handle_t *handle,
3414 struct inode *inode,
3415 struct ext4_map_blocks *map,
3416 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath,
3417 int flags)
3418{
3419 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
3420 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi;
3421 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
3422 struct ext4_map_blocks split_map;
3423 struct ext4_extent zero_ex1, zero_ex2;
3424 struct ext4_extent *ex, *abut_ex;
3425 ext4_lblk_t ee_block, eof_block;
3426 unsigned int ee_len, depth, map_len = map->m_len;
3427 int allocated = 0, max_zeroout = 0;
3428 int err = 0;
3429 int split_flag = EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID2;
3430
3431 ext_debug("ext4_ext_convert_to_initialized: inode %lu, logical"
3432 "block %llu, max_blocks %u\n", inode->i_ino,
3433 (unsigned long long)map->m_lblk, map_len);
3434
3435 sbi = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb);
3436 eof_block = (inode->i_size + inode->i_sb->s_blocksize - 1) >>
3437 inode->i_sb->s_blocksize_bits;
3438 if (eof_block < map->m_lblk + map_len)
3439 eof_block = map->m_lblk + map_len;
3440
3441 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3442 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
3443 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3444 ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
3445 ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
3446 zero_ex1.ee_len = 0;
3447 zero_ex2.ee_len = 0;
3448
3449 trace_ext4_ext_convert_to_initialized_enter(inode, map, ex);
3450
3451 /* Pre-conditions */
3452 BUG_ON(!ext4_ext_is_unwritten(ex));
3453 BUG_ON(!in_range(map->m_lblk, ee_block, ee_len));
3454
3455 /*
3456 * Attempt to transfer newly initialized blocks from the currently
3457 * unwritten extent to its neighbor. This is much cheaper
3458 * than an insertion followed by a merge as those involve costly
3459 * memmove() calls. Transferring to the left is the common case in
3460 * steady state for workloads doing fallocate(FALLOC_FL_KEEP_SIZE)
3461 * followed by append writes.
3462 *
3463 * Limitations of the current logic:
3464 * - L1: we do not deal with writes covering the whole extent.
3465 * This would require removing the extent if the transfer
3466 * is possible.
3467 * - L2: we only attempt to merge with an extent stored in the
3468 * same extent tree node.
3469 */
3470 if ((map->m_lblk == ee_block) &&
3471 /* See if we can merge left */
3472 (map_len < ee_len) && /*L1*/
3473 (ex > EXT_FIRST_EXTENT(eh))) { /*L2*/
3474 ext4_lblk_t prev_lblk;
3475 ext4_fsblk_t prev_pblk, ee_pblk;
3476 unsigned int prev_len;
3477
3478 abut_ex = ex - 1;
3479 prev_lblk = le32_to_cpu(abut_ex->ee_block);
3480 prev_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(abut_ex);
3481 prev_pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(abut_ex);
3482 ee_pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex);
3483
3484 /*
3485 * A transfer of blocks from 'ex' to 'abut_ex' is allowed
3486 * upon those conditions:
3487 * - C1: abut_ex is initialized,
3488 * - C2: abut_ex is logically abutting ex,
3489 * - C3: abut_ex is physically abutting ex,
3490 * - C4: abut_ex can receive the additional blocks without
3491 * overflowing the (initialized) length limit.
3492 */
3493 if ((!ext4_ext_is_unwritten(abut_ex)) && /*C1*/
3494 ((prev_lblk + prev_len) == ee_block) && /*C2*/
3495 ((prev_pblk + prev_len) == ee_pblk) && /*C3*/
3496 (prev_len < (EXT_INIT_MAX_LEN - map_len))) { /*C4*/
3497 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + depth);
3498 if (err)
3499 goto out;
3500
3501 trace_ext4_ext_convert_to_initialized_fastpath(inode,
3502 map, ex, abut_ex);
3503
3504 /* Shift the start of ex by 'map_len' blocks */
3505 ex->ee_block = cpu_to_le32(ee_block + map_len);
3506 ext4_ext_store_pblock(ex, ee_pblk + map_len);
3507 ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(ee_len - map_len);
3508 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex); /* Restore the flag */
3509
3510 /* Extend abut_ex by 'map_len' blocks */
3511 abut_ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(prev_len + map_len);
3512
3513 /* Result: number of initialized blocks past m_lblk */
3514 allocated = map_len;
3515 }
3516 } else if (((map->m_lblk + map_len) == (ee_block + ee_len)) &&
3517 (map_len < ee_len) && /*L1*/
3518 ex < EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh)) { /*L2*/
3519 /* See if we can merge right */
3520 ext4_lblk_t next_lblk;
3521 ext4_fsblk_t next_pblk, ee_pblk;
3522 unsigned int next_len;
3523
3524 abut_ex = ex + 1;
3525 next_lblk = le32_to_cpu(abut_ex->ee_block);
3526 next_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(abut_ex);
3527 next_pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(abut_ex);
3528 ee_pblk = ext4_ext_pblock(ex);
3529
3530 /*
3531 * A transfer of blocks from 'ex' to 'abut_ex' is allowed
3532 * upon those conditions:
3533 * - C1: abut_ex is initialized,
3534 * - C2: abut_ex is logically abutting ex,
3535 * - C3: abut_ex is physically abutting ex,
3536 * - C4: abut_ex can receive the additional blocks without
3537 * overflowing the (initialized) length limit.
3538 */
3539 if ((!ext4_ext_is_unwritten(abut_ex)) && /*C1*/
3540 ((map->m_lblk + map_len) == next_lblk) && /*C2*/
3541 ((ee_pblk + ee_len) == next_pblk) && /*C3*/
3542 (next_len < (EXT_INIT_MAX_LEN - map_len))) { /*C4*/
3543 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + depth);
3544 if (err)
3545 goto out;
3546
3547 trace_ext4_ext_convert_to_initialized_fastpath(inode,
3548 map, ex, abut_ex);
3549
3550 /* Shift the start of abut_ex by 'map_len' blocks */
3551 abut_ex->ee_block = cpu_to_le32(next_lblk - map_len);
3552 ext4_ext_store_pblock(abut_ex, next_pblk - map_len);
3553 ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(ee_len - map_len);
3554 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex); /* Restore the flag */
3555
3556 /* Extend abut_ex by 'map_len' blocks */
3557 abut_ex->ee_len = cpu_to_le16(next_len + map_len);
3558
3559 /* Result: number of initialized blocks past m_lblk */
3560 allocated = map_len;
3561 }
3562 }
3563 if (allocated) {
3564 /* Mark the block containing both extents as dirty */
3565 ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + depth);
3566
3567 /* Update path to point to the right extent */
3568 path[depth].p_ext = abut_ex;
3569 goto out;
3570 } else
3571 allocated = ee_len - (map->m_lblk - ee_block);
3572
3573 WARN_ON(map->m_lblk < ee_block);
3574 /*
3575 * It is safe to convert extent to initialized via explicit
3576 * zeroout only if extent is fully inside i_size or new_size.
3577 */
3578 split_flag |= ee_block + ee_len <= eof_block ? EXT4_EXT_MAY_ZEROOUT : 0;
3579
3580 if (EXT4_EXT_MAY_ZEROOUT & split_flag)
3581 max_zeroout = sbi->s_extent_max_zeroout_kb >>
3582 (inode->i_sb->s_blocksize_bits - 10);
3583
3584 if (ext4_encrypted_inode(inode))
3585 max_zeroout = 0;
3586
3587 /*
3588 * five cases:
3589 * 1. split the extent into three extents.
3590 * 2. split the extent into two extents, zeroout the head of the first
3591 * extent.
3592 * 3. split the extent into two extents, zeroout the tail of the second
3593 * extent.
3594 * 4. split the extent into two extents with out zeroout.
3595 * 5. no splitting needed, just possibly zeroout the head and / or the
3596 * tail of the extent.
3597 */
3598 split_map.m_lblk = map->m_lblk;
3599 split_map.m_len = map->m_len;
3600
3601 if (max_zeroout && (allocated > split_map.m_len)) {
3602 if (allocated <= max_zeroout) {
3603 /* case 3 or 5 */
3604 zero_ex1.ee_block =
3605 cpu_to_le32(split_map.m_lblk +
3606 split_map.m_len);
3607 zero_ex1.ee_len =
3608 cpu_to_le16(allocated - split_map.m_len);
3609 ext4_ext_store_pblock(&zero_ex1,
3610 ext4_ext_pblock(ex) + split_map.m_lblk +
3611 split_map.m_len - ee_block);
3612 err = ext4_ext_zeroout(inode, &zero_ex1);
3613 if (err)
3614 goto out;
3615 split_map.m_len = allocated;
3616 }
3617 if (split_map.m_lblk - ee_block + split_map.m_len <
3618 max_zeroout) {
3619 /* case 2 or 5 */
3620 if (split_map.m_lblk != ee_block) {
3621 zero_ex2.ee_block = ex->ee_block;
3622 zero_ex2.ee_len = cpu_to_le16(split_map.m_lblk -
3623 ee_block);
3624 ext4_ext_store_pblock(&zero_ex2,
3625 ext4_ext_pblock(ex));
3626 err = ext4_ext_zeroout(inode, &zero_ex2);
3627 if (err)
3628 goto out;
3629 }
3630
3631 split_map.m_len += split_map.m_lblk - ee_block;
3632 split_map.m_lblk = ee_block;
3633 allocated = map->m_len;
3634 }
3635 }
3636
3637 err = ext4_split_extent(handle, inode, ppath, &split_map, split_flag,
3638 flags);
3639 if (err > 0)
3640 err = 0;
3641out:
3642 /* If we have gotten a failure, don't zero out status tree */
3643 if (!err) {
3644 err = ext4_zeroout_es(inode, &zero_ex1);
3645 if (!err)
3646 err = ext4_zeroout_es(inode, &zero_ex2);
3647 }
3648 return err ? err : allocated;
3649}
3650
3651/*
3652 * This function is called by ext4_ext_map_blocks() from
3653 * ext4_get_blocks_dio_write() when DIO to write
3654 * to an unwritten extent.
3655 *
3656 * Writing to an unwritten extent may result in splitting the unwritten
3657 * extent into multiple initialized/unwritten extents (up to three)
3658 * There are three possibilities:
3659 * a> There is no split required: Entire extent should be unwritten
3660 * b> Splits in two extents: Write is happening at either end of the extent
3661 * c> Splits in three extents: Somone is writing in middle of the extent
3662 *
3663 * This works the same way in the case of initialized -> unwritten conversion.
3664 *
3665 * One of more index blocks maybe needed if the extent tree grow after
3666 * the unwritten extent split. To prevent ENOSPC occur at the IO
3667 * complete, we need to split the unwritten extent before DIO submit
3668 * the IO. The unwritten extent called at this time will be split
3669 * into three unwritten extent(at most). After IO complete, the part
3670 * being filled will be convert to initialized by the end_io callback function
3671 * via ext4_convert_unwritten_extents().
3672 *
3673 * Returns the size of unwritten extent to be written on success.
3674 */
3675static int ext4_split_convert_extents(handle_t *handle,
3676 struct inode *inode,
3677 struct ext4_map_blocks *map,
3678 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath,
3679 int flags)
3680{
3681 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
3682 ext4_lblk_t eof_block;
3683 ext4_lblk_t ee_block;
3684 struct ext4_extent *ex;
3685 unsigned int ee_len;
3686 int split_flag = 0, depth;
3687
3688 ext_debug("%s: inode %lu, logical block %llu, max_blocks %u\n",
3689 __func__, inode->i_ino,
3690 (unsigned long long)map->m_lblk, map->m_len);
3691
3692 eof_block = (inode->i_size + inode->i_sb->s_blocksize - 1) >>
3693 inode->i_sb->s_blocksize_bits;
3694 if (eof_block < map->m_lblk + map->m_len)
3695 eof_block = map->m_lblk + map->m_len;
3696 /*
3697 * It is safe to convert extent to initialized via explicit
3698 * zeroout only if extent is fully insde i_size or new_size.
3699 */
3700 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3701 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3702 ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
3703 ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
3704
3705 /* Convert to unwritten */
3706 if (flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_CONVERT_UNWRITTEN) {
3707 split_flag |= EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID1;
3708 /* Convert to initialized */
3709 } else if (flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_CONVERT) {
3710 split_flag |= ee_block + ee_len <= eof_block ?
3711 EXT4_EXT_MAY_ZEROOUT : 0;
3712 split_flag |= (EXT4_EXT_MARK_UNWRIT2 | EXT4_EXT_DATA_VALID2);
3713 }
3714 flags |= EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_PRE_IO;
3715 return ext4_split_extent(handle, inode, ppath, map, split_flag, flags);
3716}
3717
3718static int ext4_convert_unwritten_extents_endio(handle_t *handle,
3719 struct inode *inode,
3720 struct ext4_map_blocks *map,
3721 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath)
3722{
3723 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
3724 struct ext4_extent *ex;
3725 ext4_lblk_t ee_block;
3726 unsigned int ee_len;
3727 int depth;
3728 int err = 0;
3729
3730 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3731 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3732 ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
3733 ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
3734
3735 ext_debug("ext4_convert_unwritten_extents_endio: inode %lu, logical"
3736 "block %llu, max_blocks %u\n", inode->i_ino,
3737 (unsigned long long)ee_block, ee_len);
3738
3739 /* If extent is larger than requested it is a clear sign that we still
3740 * have some extent state machine issues left. So extent_split is still
3741 * required.
3742 * TODO: Once all related issues will be fixed this situation should be
3743 * illegal.
3744 */
3745 if (ee_block != map->m_lblk || ee_len > map->m_len) {
3746#ifdef EXT4_DEBUG
3747 ext4_warning("Inode (%ld) finished: extent logical block %llu,"
3748 " len %u; IO logical block %llu, len %u",
3749 inode->i_ino, (unsigned long long)ee_block, ee_len,
3750 (unsigned long long)map->m_lblk, map->m_len);
3751#endif
3752 err = ext4_split_convert_extents(handle, inode, map, ppath,
3753 EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_CONVERT);
3754 if (err < 0)
3755 return err;
3756 path = ext4_find_extent(inode, map->m_lblk, ppath, 0);
3757 if (IS_ERR(path))
3758 return PTR_ERR(path);
3759 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3760 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3761 }
3762
3763 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + depth);
3764 if (err)
3765 goto out;
3766 /* first mark the extent as initialized */
3767 ext4_ext_mark_initialized(ex);
3768
3769 /* note: ext4_ext_correct_indexes() isn't needed here because
3770 * borders are not changed
3771 */
3772 ext4_ext_try_to_merge(handle, inode, path, ex);
3773
3774 /* Mark modified extent as dirty */
3775 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + path->p_depth);
3776out:
3777 ext4_ext_show_leaf(inode, path);
3778 return err;
3779}
3780
3781/*
3782 * Handle EOFBLOCKS_FL flag, clearing it if necessary
3783 */
3784static int check_eofblocks_fl(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
3785 ext4_lblk_t lblk,
3786 struct ext4_ext_path *path,
3787 unsigned int len)
3788{
3789 int i, depth;
3790 struct ext4_extent_header *eh;
3791 struct ext4_extent *last_ex;
3792
3793 if (!ext4_test_inode_flag(inode, EXT4_INODE_EOFBLOCKS))
3794 return 0;
3795
3796 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3797 eh = path[depth].p_hdr;
3798
3799 /*
3800 * We're going to remove EOFBLOCKS_FL entirely in future so we
3801 * do not care for this case anymore. Simply remove the flag
3802 * if there are no extents.
3803 */
3804 if (unlikely(!eh->eh_entries))
3805 goto out;
3806 last_ex = EXT_LAST_EXTENT(eh);
3807 /*
3808 * We should clear the EOFBLOCKS_FL flag if we are writing the
3809 * last block in the last extent in the file. We test this by
3810 * first checking to see if the caller to
3811 * ext4_ext_get_blocks() was interested in the last block (or
3812 * a block beyond the last block) in the current extent. If
3813 * this turns out to be false, we can bail out from this
3814 * function immediately.
3815 */
3816 if (lblk + len < le32_to_cpu(last_ex->ee_block) +
3817 ext4_ext_get_actual_len(last_ex))
3818 return 0;
3819 /*
3820 * If the caller does appear to be planning to write at or
3821 * beyond the end of the current extent, we then test to see
3822 * if the current extent is the last extent in the file, by
3823 * checking to make sure it was reached via the rightmost node
3824 * at each level of the tree.
3825 */
3826 for (i = depth-1; i >= 0; i--)
3827 if (path[i].p_idx != EXT_LAST_INDEX(path[i].p_hdr))
3828 return 0;
3829out:
3830 ext4_clear_inode_flag(inode, EXT4_INODE_EOFBLOCKS);
3831 return ext4_mark_inode_dirty(handle, inode);
3832}
3833
3834/**
3835 * ext4_find_delalloc_range: find delayed allocated block in the given range.
3836 *
3837 * Return 1 if there is a delalloc block in the range, otherwise 0.
3838 */
3839int ext4_find_delalloc_range(struct inode *inode,
3840 ext4_lblk_t lblk_start,
3841 ext4_lblk_t lblk_end)
3842{
3843 struct extent_status es;
3844
3845 ext4_es_find_delayed_extent_range(inode, lblk_start, lblk_end, &es);
3846 if (es.es_len == 0)
3847 return 0; /* there is no delay extent in this tree */
3848 else if (es.es_lblk <= lblk_start &&
3849 lblk_start < es.es_lblk + es.es_len)
3850 return 1;
3851 else if (lblk_start <= es.es_lblk && es.es_lblk <= lblk_end)
3852 return 1;
3853 else
3854 return 0;
3855}
3856
3857int ext4_find_delalloc_cluster(struct inode *inode, ext4_lblk_t lblk)
3858{
3859 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb);
3860 ext4_lblk_t lblk_start, lblk_end;
3861 lblk_start = EXT4_LBLK_CMASK(sbi, lblk);
3862 lblk_end = lblk_start + sbi->s_cluster_ratio - 1;
3863
3864 return ext4_find_delalloc_range(inode, lblk_start, lblk_end);
3865}
3866
3867/**
3868 * Determines how many complete clusters (out of those specified by the 'map')
3869 * are under delalloc and were reserved quota for.
3870 * This function is called when we are writing out the blocks that were
3871 * originally written with their allocation delayed, but then the space was
3872 * allocated using fallocate() before the delayed allocation could be resolved.
3873 * The cases to look for are:
3874 * ('=' indicated delayed allocated blocks
3875 * '-' indicates non-delayed allocated blocks)
3876 * (a) partial clusters towards beginning and/or end outside of allocated range
3877 * are not delalloc'ed.
3878 * Ex:
3879 * |----c---=|====c====|====c====|===-c----|
3880 * |++++++ allocated ++++++|
3881 * ==> 4 complete clusters in above example
3882 *
3883 * (b) partial cluster (outside of allocated range) towards either end is
3884 * marked for delayed allocation. In this case, we will exclude that
3885 * cluster.
3886 * Ex:
3887 * |----====c========|========c========|
3888 * |++++++ allocated ++++++|
3889 * ==> 1 complete clusters in above example
3890 *
3891 * Ex:
3892 * |================c================|
3893 * |++++++ allocated ++++++|
3894 * ==> 0 complete clusters in above example
3895 *
3896 * The ext4_da_update_reserve_space will be called only if we
3897 * determine here that there were some "entire" clusters that span
3898 * this 'allocated' range.
3899 * In the non-bigalloc case, this function will just end up returning num_blks
3900 * without ever calling ext4_find_delalloc_range.
3901 */
3902static unsigned int
3903get_reserved_cluster_alloc(struct inode *inode, ext4_lblk_t lblk_start,
3904 unsigned int num_blks)
3905{
3906 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(inode->i_sb);
3907 ext4_lblk_t alloc_cluster_start, alloc_cluster_end;
3908 ext4_lblk_t lblk_from, lblk_to, c_offset;
3909 unsigned int allocated_clusters = 0;
3910
3911 alloc_cluster_start = EXT4_B2C(sbi, lblk_start);
3912 alloc_cluster_end = EXT4_B2C(sbi, lblk_start + num_blks - 1);
3913
3914 /* max possible clusters for this allocation */
3915 allocated_clusters = alloc_cluster_end - alloc_cluster_start + 1;
3916
3917 trace_ext4_get_reserved_cluster_alloc(inode, lblk_start, num_blks);
3918
3919 /* Check towards left side */
3920 c_offset = EXT4_LBLK_COFF(sbi, lblk_start);
3921 if (c_offset) {
3922 lblk_from = EXT4_LBLK_CMASK(sbi, lblk_start);
3923 lblk_to = lblk_from + c_offset - 1;
3924
3925 if (ext4_find_delalloc_range(inode, lblk_from, lblk_to))
3926 allocated_clusters--;
3927 }
3928
3929 /* Now check towards right. */
3930 c_offset = EXT4_LBLK_COFF(sbi, lblk_start + num_blks);
3931 if (allocated_clusters && c_offset) {
3932 lblk_from = lblk_start + num_blks;
3933 lblk_to = lblk_from + (sbi->s_cluster_ratio - c_offset) - 1;
3934
3935 if (ext4_find_delalloc_range(inode, lblk_from, lblk_to))
3936 allocated_clusters--;
3937 }
3938
3939 return allocated_clusters;
3940}
3941
3942static int
3943convert_initialized_extent(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
3944 struct ext4_map_blocks *map,
3945 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath,
3946 unsigned int allocated)
3947{
3948 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
3949 struct ext4_extent *ex;
3950 ext4_lblk_t ee_block;
3951 unsigned int ee_len;
3952 int depth;
3953 int err = 0;
3954
3955 /*
3956 * Make sure that the extent is no bigger than we support with
3957 * unwritten extent
3958 */
3959 if (map->m_len > EXT_UNWRITTEN_MAX_LEN)
3960 map->m_len = EXT_UNWRITTEN_MAX_LEN / 2;
3961
3962 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3963 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3964 ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
3965 ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
3966
3967 ext_debug("%s: inode %lu, logical"
3968 "block %llu, max_blocks %u\n", __func__, inode->i_ino,
3969 (unsigned long long)ee_block, ee_len);
3970
3971 if (ee_block != map->m_lblk || ee_len > map->m_len) {
3972 err = ext4_split_convert_extents(handle, inode, map, ppath,
3973 EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_CONVERT_UNWRITTEN);
3974 if (err < 0)
3975 return err;
3976 path = ext4_find_extent(inode, map->m_lblk, ppath, 0);
3977 if (IS_ERR(path))
3978 return PTR_ERR(path);
3979 depth = ext_depth(inode);
3980 ex = path[depth].p_ext;
3981 if (!ex) {
3982 EXT4_ERROR_INODE(inode, "unexpected hole at %lu",
3983 (unsigned long) map->m_lblk);
3984 return -EFSCORRUPTED;
3985 }
3986 }
3987
3988 err = ext4_ext_get_access(handle, inode, path + depth);
3989 if (err)
3990 return err;
3991 /* first mark the extent as unwritten */
3992 ext4_ext_mark_unwritten(ex);
3993
3994 /* note: ext4_ext_correct_indexes() isn't needed here because
3995 * borders are not changed
3996 */
3997 ext4_ext_try_to_merge(handle, inode, path, ex);
3998
3999 /* Mark modified extent as dirty */
4000 err = ext4_ext_dirty(handle, inode, path + path->p_depth);
4001 if (err)
4002 return err;
4003 ext4_ext_show_leaf(inode, path);
4004
4005 ext4_update_inode_fsync_trans(handle, inode, 1);
4006 err = check_eofblocks_fl(handle, inode, map->m_lblk, path, map->m_len);
4007 if (err)
4008 return err;
4009 map->m_flags |= EXT4_MAP_UNWRITTEN;
4010 if (allocated > map->m_len)
4011 allocated = map->m_len;
4012 map->m_len = allocated;
4013 return allocated;
4014}
4015
4016static int
4017ext4_ext_handle_unwritten_extents(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
4018 struct ext4_map_blocks *map,
4019 struct ext4_ext_path **ppath, int flags,
4020 unsigned int allocated, ext4_fsblk_t newblock)
4021{
4022 struct ext4_ext_path *path = *ppath;
4023 int ret = 0;
4024 int err = 0;
4025
4026 ext_debug("ext4_ext_handle_unwritten_extents: inode %lu, logical "
4027 "block %llu, max_blocks %u, flags %x, allocated %u\n",
4028 inode->i_ino, (unsigned long long)map->m_lblk, map->m_len,
4029 flags, allocated);
4030 ext4_ext_show_leaf(inode, path);
4031
4032 /*
4033 * When writing into unwritten space, we should not fail to
4034 * allocate metadata blocks for the new extent block if needed.
4035 */
4036 flags |= EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_METADATA_NOFAIL;
4037
4038 trace_ext4_ext_handle_unwritten_extents(inode, map, flags,
4039 allocated, newblock);
4040
4041 /* get_block() before submit the IO, split the extent */
4042 if (flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_PRE_IO) {
4043 ret = ext4_split_convert_extents(handle, inode, map, ppath,
4044 flags | EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_CONVERT);
4045 if (ret <= 0)
4046 goto out;
4047 map->m_flags |= EXT4_MAP_UNWRITTEN;
4048 goto out;
4049 }
4050 /* IO end_io complete, convert the filled extent to written */
4051 if (flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_CONVERT) {
4052 if (flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_ZERO) {
4053 if (allocated > map->m_len)
4054 allocated = map->m_len;
4055 err = ext4_issue_zeroout(inode, map->m_lblk, newblock,
4056 allocated);
4057 if (err < 0)
4058 goto out2;
4059 }
4060 ret = ext4_convert_unwritten_extents_endio(handle, inode, map,
4061 ppath);
4062 if (ret >= 0) {
4063 ext4_update_inode_fsync_trans(handle, inode, 1);
4064 err = check_eofblocks_fl(handle, inode, map->m_lblk,
4065 path, map->m_len);
4066 } else
4067 err = ret;
4068 map->m_flags |= EXT4_MAP_MAPPED;
4069 map->m_pblk = newblock;
4070 if (allocated > map->m_len)
4071 allocated = map->m_len;
4072 map->m_len = allocated;
4073 goto out2;
4074 }
4075 /* buffered IO case */
4076 /*
4077 * repeat fallocate creation request
4078 * we already have an unwritten extent
4079 */
4080 if (flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_UNWRIT_EXT) {
4081 map->m_flags |= EXT4_MAP_UNWRITTEN;
4082 goto map_out;
4083 }
4084
4085 /* buffered READ or buffered write_begin() lookup */
4086 if ((flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_CREATE) == 0) {
4087 /*
4088 * We have blocks reserved already. We
4089 * return allocated blocks so that delalloc
4090 * won't do block reservation for us. But
4091 * the buffer head will be unmapped so that
4092 * a read from the block returns 0s.
4093 */
4094 map->m_flags |= EXT4_MAP_UNWRITTEN;
4095 goto out1;
4096 }
4097
4098 /* buffered write, writepage time, convert*/
4099 ret = ext4_ext_convert_to_initialized(handle, inode, map, ppath, flags);
4100 if (ret >= 0)
4101 ext4_update_inode_fsync_trans(handle, inode, 1);
4102out:
4103 if (ret <= 0) {
4104 err = ret;
4105 goto out2;
4106 } else
4107 allocated = ret;
4108 map->m_flags |= EXT4_MAP_NEW;
4109 /*
4110 * if we allocated more blocks than requested
4111 * we need to make sure we unmap the extra block
4112 * allocated. The actual needed block will get
4113 * unmapped later when we find the buffer_head marked
4114 * new.
4115 */
4116 if (allocated > map->m_len) {
4117 clean_bdev_aliases(inode->i_sb->s_bdev, newblock + map->m_len,
4118 allocated - map->m_len);
4119 allocated = map->m_len;
4120 }
4121 map->m_len = allocated;
4122
4123 /*
4124 * If we have done fallocate with the offset that is already
4125 * delayed allocated, we would have block reservation
4126 * and quota reservation done in the delayed write path.
4127 * But fallocate would have already updated quota and block
4128 * count for this offset. So cancel these reservation
4129 */
4130 if (flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_DELALLOC_RESERVE) {
4131 unsigned int reserved_clusters;
4132 reserved_clusters = get_reserved_cluster_alloc(inode,
4133 map->m_lblk, map->m_len);
4134 if (reserved_clusters)
4135 ext4_da_update_reserve_space(inode,
4136 reserved_clusters,
4137 0);
4138 }
4139
4140map_out:
4141 map->m_flags |= EXT4_MAP_MAPPED;
4142 if ((flags & EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_KEEP_SIZE) == 0) {
4143 err = check_eofblocks_fl(handle, inode, map->m_lblk, path,
4144 map->m_len);
4145 if (err < 0)
4146 goto out2;
4147 }
4148out1:
4149 if (allocated > map->m_len)
4150 allocated = map->m_len;
4151 ext4_ext_show_leaf(inode, path);
4152 map->m_pblk = newblock;
4153 map->m_len = allocated;
4154out2:
4155 return err ? err : allocated;
4156}

4158/*
4159 * get_implied_cluster_alloc - check to see if the requested
4160 * allocation (in the map structure) overlaps with a cluster already
4161 * allocated in an extent.
4162 * @sb The filesystem superblock structure
4163 * @map The requested lblk->pblk mapping
4164 * @ex The extent structure which might contain an implied
4165 * cluster allocation
4166 *
4167 * This function is called by ext4_ext_map_blocks() after we failed to
4168 * find blocks that were already in the inode's extent tree. Hence,
4169 * we know that the beginning of the requested region cannot overlap
4170 * the extent from the inode's extent tree. There are three cases we
4171 * want to catch. The first is this case:
4172 *
4173 * |--- cluster # N--|
4174 * |--- extent ---| |---- requested region ---|
4175 * |==========|
4176 *
4177 * The second case that we need to test for is this one:
4178 *
4179 * |--------- cluster # N ----------------|
4180 * |--- requested region --| |------- extent ----|
4181 * |=======================|
4182 *
4183 * The third case is when the requested region lies between two extents
4184 * within the same cluster:
4185 * |------------- cluster # N-------------|
4186 * |----- ex -----| |---- ex_right ----|
4187 * |------ requested region ------|
4188 * |================|
4189 *
4190 * In each of the above cases, we need to set the map->m_pblk and
4191 * map->m_len so it corresponds to the return the extent labelled as
4192 * "|====|" from cluster #N, since it is already in use for data in
4193 * cluster EXT4_B2C(sbi, map->m_lblk). We will then return 1 to
4194 * signal to ext4_ext_map_blocks() that map->m_pblk should be treated
4195 * as a new "allocated" block region. Otherwise, we will return 0 and
4196 * ext4_ext_map_blocks() will then allocate one or more new clusters
4197 * by calling ext4_mb_new_blocks().
4198 */
4199static int get_implied_cluster_alloc(struct super_block *sb,
4200 struct ext4_map_blocks *map,
4201 struct ext4_extent *ex,
4202 struct ext4_ext_path *path)
4203{
4204 struct ext4_sb_info *sbi = EXT4_SB(sb);
4205 ext4_lblk_t c_offset = EXT4_LBLK_COFF(sbi, map->m_lblk);
4206 ext4_lblk_t ex_cluster_start, ex_cluster_end;
4207 ext4_lblk_t rr_cluster_start;
4208 ext4_lblk_t ee_block = le32_to_cpu(ex->ee_block);
4209 ext4_fsblk_t ee_start = ext4_ext_pblock(ex);
4210 unsigned short ee_len = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(ex);
4211
4212 /* The extent passed in that we are trying to match */
4213 ex_cluster_start = EXT4_B2C(sbi, ee_block);
4214 ex_cluster_end = EXT4_B2C(sbi, ee_block + ee_len - 1);
4215
4216 /* The requested region passed into ext4_map_blocks() */
4217 rr_cluster_start = EXT4_B2C(sbi, map->m_lblk);
4218
4219 if ((rr_cluster_start == ex_cluster_end) ||
4220 (rr_cluster_start == ex_cluster_start)) {
4221 if (rr_cluster_start == ex_cluster_end)
4222 ee_start += ee_len - 1;
4223 map->m_pblk = EXT4_PBLK_CMASK(sbi, ee_start) + c_offset;
4224 map->m_len = min(map->m_len,
4225 (unsigned) sbi->s_cluster_ratio - c_offset);
4226 /*
4227 * Check for and handle this case:
4228 *
4229 * |--------- cluster # N-------------|
4230 * |------- extent ----|
4231 * |--- requested region ---|
4232 * |===========|
4233 */
4234
4235 if (map->m_lblk < ee_block)
4236 map->m_len = min(map->m_len, ee_block - map->m_lblk);
4237
4238 /*
4239 * Check for the case where there is already another allocated
4240 * block to the right of 'ex' but before the end of the cluster.
4241 *
4242 * |------------- cluster # N-------------|
4243 * |----- ex -----| |---- ex_right ----|
4244 * |------ requested region ------|
4245 * |================|
4246 */
4247 if (map->m_lblk > ee_block) {
4248 ext4_lblk_t next = ext4_ext_next_allocated_block(path);
4249 map->m_len = min(map->m_len, next - map->m_lblk);
4250 }
4251
4252 trace_ext4_get_implied_cluster_alloc_exit(sb, map, 1);
4253 return 1;
4254 }
4255
4256 trace_ext4_get_implied_cluster_alloc_exit(sb, map, 0);
4257 return 0;
4258}
